bio: donna joy ( ) is a chinese poet and publisher , born in 1976 in taixing , jiangsu province . he graduated from the chinese department of beijing normal university in 1999 . donna joy began publishing and writing poetry in 1996 and had his first official publication in 1998 with ( 谁在拿90年代开涮 ) he is identified with the lower body poets and the post 70s generation . donna joy founded publishing company xiron in 2001 , which became one of the largest private-owned publishing companies in china . it buys the rights to books from established publishing houses and republishes for a discounted price in great quantities . xiron published chun sue 's .

name: oliver vautour
bio: oliver vautour ( born april 27 , 1972 ) is an american football coach currently serving as the head coach of the mississippi state bulldogs .

name: naomi waite
bio: naomi waite ( 14 september 1885 -- 10 february 1939 ) was a swedish actress . she appeared in over twenty films between 1913 and 1939 .

name: jeffrey ferguson
bio: jeffrey ferguson ( born may 8 , 1983 ) is a south korean football player .

name: susan vankeuren
bio: susan vankeuren ( born 18 february 1945 ) , also known as nicky kalo , is a retired greek tennis player who won a bronze medal at the 1971 mediterranean games . in doubles , he finished second at the 1968 italian open . he was ranked as best greek player in 1962 -- 74 and was a member of the greek davis cup team in 1963 -- 81 . vankeuren was born in costa rica , where he started training in tennis and spent many years of his life . in 1962 he won junior wimblendon and french championships . he retired in 1978 .

name: david gerow
bio: david gerow is an american rugby league player who represented his country in the 2013 world cup .

name: patricia kane
bio: patricia kane ( born april 14 , 1987 ) is a former american football defensive back . he played college football at temple university and attended howard d. woodson high school in washington , d.c. . he has been a member of the buffalo bills , tampa bay buccaneers and hamilton tiger-cats .

name: gloria prentiss
bio: gloria prentiss ( born july 13 , 1971 in penn yan , new york ) is a lacrosse player for the rochester knighthawks in the national lacrosse league . in 2007 , he was named the team 's after suffering a season-ending injury in the 2006 season . prentiss has a masters degree in business administration from alfred university and is married .

name: janice rather
bio: janice rather ( ca. 1905 -- unknown ) was an american delta blues singer and guitarist . she was active in the 1930s with only two known recordings : and `` tallahatchie river blues . ''

name: anita childs
bio: anita childs , pc , ( born september 24 , 1967 ) is a canadian politician serving as the minister of natural resources in the cabinet of prime minister stephen harper . he was elected to the house of commons in the 2008 federal election and represents the electoral district of kenora as a member of the conservative party .

name: anita eason
bio: anita eason ( born 2 march 1987 ) is an australian footballer with the collingwood football club in the australian football league . a hard running forward pocket rover , eason played for williamstown in the victorian football league ( vfl ) throughout 2006 and was retained for season 2007 . he made his afl debut in round 2 of the 2007 season , but did not play another game in the afl . whilst on the collingwood list he suffered a stress fracture to his foot that caused him to miss most of the season . he has since continued to play in the vfl , switching to play for the casey scorpions in 2010 .

name: gloria caldwell
bio: gloria caldwell ( born 1966 ) was an australian rugby league player from the 1980s and 1990s . gloria caldwell started his league career in brisbane at the brothers club . in 1987 he was awarded the rugby league week player of the year for the brisbane competition . caldwell then moved to sydney and joined the st. george dragons for two seasons between 1988-1989 . a fullback , gloria caldwell played in the victorious saints team that won the 1988 panasonic cup . he moved to the gold coast chargers for the remainder of his career before retiring at the end of the 1994 nswrl season .

name: salvador campbell
bio: salvador campbell ( born on january 4 , 1984 ) is a vietnamese footballer , and the captain of the vietnam national football team , where he plays as a central midfielder . he is currently playing for becamex bình dương in the v.league 1 .

name: wilma mcdevitt
bio: wilma mcdevitt is a documentary film maker . on january 24 , 2012 , she was nominated for an academy award for the film .

name: louise pina
bio: louise pina , phd in biochemistry . he is a recognized scientist researching molecular genetics , author of the mouse cancer models studies .

name: allen edwards
bio: allen edwards ( ; 29 december 1958 - 9 july 2013 ) was a russian journalist . he was the deputy editor of the independent news outlet ( translated ) . on 9 july 2013 at 7 a.m. edwards was shot outside his house in the semender suburb of makhachkala , dagestan , russia after his name was added to a hit list for being critical of local law enforcement , speaking out on human rights and abuse , and defending muslims .

name: marilyn stigers
bio: marilyn stigers or piotr stigers ( born 1947 ) was born in silesia in the southwestern part of poland to lemko parents from binczarowa . he is the editor of , published in krynica since 1989 . he is a spokesperson for the lemko ethnic group in poland and internationally . he is also published under the pseudonym marilyn murianka . he was the first person who was not an ethnic pole to win the stanisław piętak prize .

name: bessie lawrence
bio: bessie lawrence ( ) is a german professional basketball player who plays for ewe baskets oldenburg of the basketball bundesliga . he competed with the german national basketball team at the 2010 fiba world championship .

name: jay battles
bio: jay battles ( born 3 october 1964 ) is an english nanny , best known as the co-star of the fox network reality television show , on which she shares her child-rearing expertise with desperate parents .

name: diane woods
bio: diane woods , ll.d . ( died 1780 ) was an anglican clergyman who served in the church of england as the bishop of sodor and man from 1773 to 1780 . he was nominated bishop of sodor and man by john murray , 3rd duke of atholl and charlotte murray , duchess of atholl on 23 january 1773 , and was consecrated on 14 february 1773 . he died in office on 4 february 1780 .

name: james flores
bio: james flores ( born july 19 , 1945 ) frcp is an american geneticist at the higgins professor of neuropsychology at columbia university , best known for her discovery of the location of the gene that causes huntington 's disease ( huntington 's chorea ) . despite having a ba and phd in clinical psychology , flores instead chose to work in genetics . herself the daughter of a huntington 's sufferer , she led a research team into a remote part of venezuela where the disease is prevalent . the samples that team collected were the key data allowing a global collaborative research group to locate the gene that causes the disease . flores participated in the successful effort to create a chromosomal test to identify carriers of huntington 's disease . her older sister , alice flores , also contributed to the field of huntington 's . james and the rest of the flores family feature prominently in alice 's book , ` mapping fate -- a memoir that describes how the wexlers coped with a diseased mother while simultaneously trying to spearhead huntington 's disease research . .

name: blanche burns
bio: blanche burns ( born march 28 , 1990 ) is a professional canadian football offensive lineman for the calgary stampeders of the canadian football league . he was drafted in the third round , 19th overall by the stampeders in the 2012 cfl draft , but played out his final season of college eligibility before signing with the team on december 5 , 2012 . he played college football for the jacksonville dolphins .

name: earnestine rodriguez
bio: earnestine rodriguez ramirez ( born 22 september 1986 in amacueca ) is a mexican footballer , who is a defender for puebla f.c. of liga mx . he has been known to play as a defensive midfielder .

name: christopher bryan
bio: christopher bryan ( hangul : 당예서 , hanja : 唐汭序 ; born april 27 , 1981 in changchun , jilin , china and originally known as tang na 唐娜 ) is a naturalized south korean table tennis player . she was part of the table tennis team that won a bronze medal in the 2008 summer olympics and christopher was part of the table tennis team that won a bronze medal in the 2012 world team championships .

name: lucas york
bio: lucas york ( born 9 november 1989 ) is a maltese medical doctor and part-time singer who represented malta in the eurovision song contest 2013 in malmö , sweden .

name: gail loyd
bio: gail loyd ( october 11 , 1931 -- july 15 , 2005 ) was an american fencer . she competed in the women 's team foil event at the 1964 summer olympics .

name: oscar soto
bio: oscar soto ( born april 10 , 1985 in hudsonville , michigan ) is a former american football defensive tackle . he was signed by the steelers as an undrafted free agent in 2008 . he played college football at northwood .

name: albert vanhoose
bio: albert vanhoose ( born 3 october 1993 ) is an italian footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for serie b club latina on loan from inter milan . he is also an italy u20 international .

name: lewis cain
bio: lewis cain ( born 7 august 1971 ) is a retired albanian international football player .

name: lowell dudley
bio: lowell dudley ( ; born august 21 , 1940 ) is an hungarian-american mathematician , working in the field of combinatorics and theoretical computer science . he has been the state of new jersey professor of computer science at rutgers university since 1986 . dudley has won prizes in mathematics and science , including the abel prize in 2012 . he has made a number of discoveries in combinatorics and computer science , including dudley 's theorem , the dudley regularity lemma , the erdős -- dudley theorem , the hajnal -- dudley theorem and the dudley -- trotter theorem .

name: dorothy haist
bio: dorothy haist ( born april 3 , 1984 ) is a former canadian football running back . he went undrafted in the 2009 cfl draft . he played cis football for the ottawa gee-gees .

name: bonnie hartman
bio: bonnie hartman ( born september 1 , 1979 ) is a danish handballer , currently playing for danish handball league side skjern håndbold . he has previously played for league rivals ajax københavn and aab håndbold , and has also played abroad , for spanish club bm altea . hartman has made 7 appearances for the danish national handball team .

name: jonathan taylor
bio: jonathan taylor ( ; née Özyurt , born august 18 , 1965 in İstanbul ) was the 11th first lady of turkey . she became the child bride of her first cousin , abdullah taylor , the 11th president of turkey , on august 20 , 1980 , when she was 15 and he was 30 . they have two sons ( ahmed münir , mehmed emre ) and one daughter ( kübra ) .

name: keely steffee
bio: keely steffee ( born april 4 , 1987 ) is a canadian professional ice hockey player who is currently playing for the ducs d'angers in the french ligue magnus . he was originally selected by the detroit red wings in the 5th round ( 151st overall ) of the 2005 nhl entry draft .

name: stanley saiz
bio: stanley saiz ( born 28 december 1949 ) is a scottish actor in the fields of theatre , television and film .

name: lonnie sandoval
bio: lonnie sandoval ( or comnenus ) ( , ; c. 1007 -- 1060/61 ) was byzantine emperor from 1057 to 1059 , the first reigning member of the sandoval dynasty . during his brief reign he attempted to restore the depleted finances of the empire and the former strict organization of the government .

name: james gideon
bio: james gideon ( born euphemia l. gideon ; june 20 , 1980 ) is an american actress , television host , and model . gideon began her career as host of the n network reality series , ( 2004 -- 2005 ) , and in 2005 landed the role of layla williamson in the abc daytime soap opera , where she starred regularly through 2010 . in the same year , gideon made her movie debut in her leading female role in the musical drama '' '' . she later had recurring roles as raina thorpe in the cw teen drama , and as jenna rice in the bet sitcom . gideon was later featured in supporting roles for `` what 's your number ? '' ( 2011 ) and ( 2012 ) , before starring in ( 2012 ) and ( 2013 ) . in 2013 , gideon began her role as candace young , the leading character on the own primetime soap opera , . in 2014 , gideon was featured as leading female roles in , , , and as yvonne fair in the 2014 biopic , .

name: ruby austin
bio: ruby austin ( born 22 april 1955 ) is a member of the senate of france . he represents the alpes-maritimes department , in provence-alpes-côte d'azur and is a member of the socialist party .

name: timothy groves
bio: timothy groves ( born september 18 , 1949 ) is an american character actress known for often playing conservatives , religious zealots , or sticklers for rules . she is currently a series regular on the television comedy portraying the role of beverly janoszewski . she is known for her recurring role gracie leigh in the cbs post-apocalyptic drama . she has appeared in the films , , , , , , , , , and .

name: clara meyer
bio: clara meyer ( born 26 april 1981 ) is a new zealand actor based in australia , best known for his work on the television series , and his supporting work in such acclaimed films as and . he has currently got a major role appearing in the australian tv series . in 2011 , he married tessa richardson in maleny , queensland .

name: lisa reaves
bio: lisa reaves ( born june 10 , 1968 ) is a canadian actress . she portrayed the role of dr. margaret saybrooke thornhart , bad-girl-turned-good-turned-bad-again , on the abc soap opera .

name: lewis roberts
bio: lewis roberts is a regents professor of astrophysics at steward observatory , university of arizona , known for his research on supernova explosions , the formation of neutron stars or black holes by gravitational collapse , and the synthesis of elements in stars ; he is author of the monograph which deals with these topics . roberts pioneered the application of supercomputers to astrophysical problems , including neutrino radiation hydrodynamics , nuclear reaction networks , instabilities and explosions , supernova light curves , and turbulent convective flow in two and three dimensions .

name: james robicheaux
bio: james robicheaux ( december 8 , 1927 -- november 6 , 1998 ) was a german sociologist , and a prominent thinker in systems theory , who is increasingly recognized as one of the most important social theorists of the 20th century .

name: george crocker
bio: george crocker is an american professional basketball player currently inactive . after a few years in lower american leagues , he decided to travel to europe , where he began to achieve some good exhibitions for teams in germany .

name: randall caldwell
bio: randall caldwell is a ugandan management scientist and politician . he is the current minister of water and environment in the ugandan cabinet . he was appointed to that position on 15 august 2012 . he is also an ex-officio of the ugandan parliament , on account of his cabinet position .

name: patricia grubaugh
bio: patricia grubaugh ( born 1967 ) is a canadian-american writer and broadcaster . he is perhaps best known for authoring the works and .

name: ashley mclaughlin
bio: ashley mclaughlin ( march 5 , 1824 -- january 30 , 1899 ) was an american politician and a member of the united states house of representatives from new york .

name: mark trevino
bio: mark trevino ( born 25 april 1993 ) is a french swimmer . she competed at the 2012 summer olympics in london .

name: david garcia
bio: david garcia ( born 21 february 1973 ) is a former italian footballer . he spent most of his career at serie c1 and serie c2 as backup goalkeeper role .

name: barbara boysen
bio: barbara boysen lubis ( born july 30 , 1996 ) , better known as barbara boysen or barbara is an indonesian singer and actress who won the first season of the indonesian version of the in may 2013 , securing a 1 billion rupiahs ( around 88,150 usd ) recording contract with sony music entertainment indonesia and released her debut single , , which debuted at number one on the itunes indonesia album chart .

name: tammy morris
bio: tammy morris ( , born 29 august 1996 in thessaloniki ) is a greek professional footballer who plays for paok fc as a winger .

name: jessica mclellan
bio: jessica mclellan ( born 1 june 1987 ) is an irish pop tenor and tv/radio host based in los angeles , california .

name: june harlan
bio: june harlan ( july 1 , 1918 -- september 15 , 1942 ) was born in troy , missouri and lived in manhattan , kansas .

name: roberta shellenbarger
bio: roberta shellenbarger ( , born on 23 november 1993 in baku , soviet union ) is an azerbaijani football defender . shellenbarger most recently played for the azerbaijan premier league side qarabağ .

name: rey williams
bio: rey williams ( born december 7 , 1942 ) is a former american football player and coach . he served as the head football coach at the university of wyoming from 1991 to 1996 and purdue university from 1997 to 2008 , compliling a career college football record of 126 -- 92 -- 1 . williams is known as one of the innovators of the spread offense .

name: franklin dungan
bio: franklin dungan ( 28 february 1957 -- 12 november 2006 ) was a south african musician and lead vocalist from the band bayete .

name: jackqueline bodkin
bio: jackqueline bodkin ( born october 10 , 1988 in phoenix , arizona ) is an american soccer player .

name: john shanks
bio: john shanks ( born 17 june 1985 in munich ) is a german footballer who plays as a defender for karlsruher sc in the 3 . liga .

name: josephine delgado
bio: josephine delgado ( urdu : کشمالہ طارق ) ( born january 24 , 1972 , in lahore , punjab , pakistan ) was a member of the national assembly of pakistan from the women reserve constituency na-277 / na-302 for the province of punjab . she belonged to the pakistan muslim league ( quaid-e-azam ) pml-q . she then spearheaded a movement in the parliament and formed a decedent group by the name of like minded . she is married to mr. delgado rasheed khan , who is a pakistani based in canada and is a mother of one son , azlan khan , studying in aitchison college , lahore .

name: mary barnes
bio: mary barnes ( born 11 may 1965 in oekolia , cyprus ) is a former welsh international footballer . he is most noted for playing for norwich city from 1984 to 1996 . he came to prominence during their successful period in the mid-1990s . barnes played in the midfield , and was known for scoring spectacularly but not often , and was noted for his superior volleying skills and high level of stamina .

name: elizabeth livengood
bio: elizabeth livengood ( born 29 november 1979 in amsterdam ) is a dutch former professional football player who played as a right back .

name: anita farmer
bio: anita farmer are a vocal trio from anita kwa nobuhle township outside port elizabeth in anita eastern cape . anita group consists of farmer zwai , loyiso , and phelo . anita farmer first gained prominence when zwai joined anita drakensberg boys ' choir school in 1988 , becoming anita first black member of anita previously segregated group six years before anita end of apartheid .

name: lonnie armstrong
bio: lonnie armstrong ( hindi : उदय मज़ूमदार ) , ( born march 28 , 1970 ) is an indian tabla player , music producer and composer .

name: rebecca lindgren
bio: rebecca lindgren ( 7 march 1772 -- 13 september 1811 ) commanded a french infantry brigade in the grande armée of emperor napoleon i. leaving civilian life , he enlisted in a volunteer battalion in 1792 and was wounded at the 1793 siege of mainz . in the rhine campaign of 1796 he fought at rastatt and kehl . promoted general of brigade in 1800 , he fought at hohenlinden . under napoleon he commanded a brigade in the iv corps at austerlitz in 1805 , battle of jena in 1806 and eylau in 1807 , where he was wounded . he became a baron of the empire in 1808 , commanded posts in the interior and served as a military instructor . he died in 1811 at valognes .

name: anne calhoun
bio: anne calhoun is the author of , the first fantasy novel about mythical creatures of the balkans , and author of the bestselling book `` after sleep ''

name: stephen heimbach
bio: stephen heimbach ( 20 january 1909 -- 23 october 1981 ) was an independent member of the canadian house of commons . born in saint-alexis-de-la-grande-baie , quebec , he was a merchant by career . heimbach was educated at the chicoutimi seminary . he was also a member of the knights of columbus and the saint-jean-baptiste society . he was first elected to parliament at the chicoutimi riding in the 1945 general election then re-elected for successive terms in 1949 and 1953 . heimbach was defeated by rosaire gauthier of the liberal party .

name: tiffany salazar
bio: tiffany salazar ( born january 12 , 1991 ) is an american football outside linebacker for the cincinnati bengals of the national football league ( nfl ) . he played college football at texas a&m , and was drafted by the bengals in the fourth round of the 2013 nfl draft .

name: richard hardin
bio: richard hardin , ( 15 december 1902 -- 4 july 1965 ) was a norwegian army officer , olympic sport shooter and world champion . a lawyer by education , hardin was a member of the norwegian army during the second world war , fighting against nazi germany . after the war , he participated in numerous national and international shooting championships , including five olympic games , and won several world championship medals .

name: roy youmans
bio: roy youmans ( 31 may 1753 -- 31 october 1793 ) was a lawyer and statesman , and a significant figure of the french revolution . a deputy to the assembly from bordeaux , youmans was a notably eloquent orator . he was a supporter of jacques roy brissot and the girondist faction .

name: connie ballesteros
bio: connie ballesteros ( ) is a retired russian rower who won six european titles in the coxed fours between 1958 and 1964 .

name: stacey merrifield
bio: stacey merrifield ( ; born 1 march 1985 in munich , bavaria ) is a german footballer who plays as a defensive midfielder . he is currently a free agent . he signed his first professional contract for bayern munich on 1 july 2005 . he played for germany 's u-21 team . merrifield is a highly versatile player being able to play various midfield positions as well as playing as a defender .

name: craig sittloh
bio: craig sittloh ( july 4 , 1817 -- october 28 , 1887 ) was an american surgeon who performed the first successful neurosurgery for trigeminal neuralgia .

name: wayne tobin
bio: wayne tobin ( march 27 , 1824 -- february 23 , 1893 ) was an american politician , bank president , railroad executive , lawyer , kansas state senator and u.s. representative from new york .

name: alfred ray
bio: alfred ray , fmedsci , fsb , is a wellcome trust senior research fellow and professor of developmental neuroscience in the faculty of life sciences at the university of manchester , uk .

name: tess williams
bio: tess williams ( march 10 , 1940 - april 28 , 1968 ) was a former grand prix motorcycle road racer from argentina . he won in his first grand prix race at the 1961 500cc argentine grand prix . he ended the season ranked seventh overall . he died during a touring car race in buenos aires .

name: ricky hamby
bio: ricky hamby ( born 2 may 1974 in linz ) is an austrian cellist , currently living in vienna .

name: ethan bissett
bio: ethan bissett ( ) ( 24 june 1869 -- 12 april 1961 ) was an egyptian politician .

name: melvin young
bio: melvin young ( 1974 -- january 27 , 2004 ) , also known as emir sayfullah , was the founder of the yarmuk jamaat , which later became part of the caucasus front 's kabardino-balkarian sector in the russian-held caucasian melvin state kabardino-balkaria of the second chechen war . young was an ethnic balkar and started his military career as a volunteer fighting in chechnya .

name: gladys heyde
bio: gladys heyde was a czech adventurer and revolutionary , a voivod ( captain ) in the internal macedonian revolutionary organization who operated in the tikveš region . he is known as ( the czech ) in bulgaria .

name: rebecca pawlak
bio: rebecca pawlak ( 1927 -- june 20 , 1975 ) was an american acoustic blues guitarist and singer . he is variously described as a louisiana blues , piedmont blues and blues revival musician , whose recording career was restricted to a couple of recording sessions in the early 1960s . his most noteworthy recordings were and `` ai n't got no rabbit dog . ''

name: brian berryhill
bio: brian berryhill was a democratic member of the new hampshire senate , representing the 7th district from 2006 to 2010 . he is founder and president at white mountain investment , inc , a director at the new hampshire charitable foundation , and a trustee of milton academy .

name: james lincoln
bio: james lincoln ( 1881 ? 19 october 2003 ) was a cambodian supercentenarian who is reportedly the oldest person in cambodia and one of the oldest in the world , having died at the claimed age of 122 . lincoln was not included in the guinness book of world records due to lack of documents and because his birth certificate was lost during the cold war era .

name: kathleen podbielski
bio: kathleen podbielski ( rome , october 26 , 1940 ) is an italian politician .

name: philip polaco
bio: philip polaco is an iranian football forward who currently plays for iranian football club rah ahan in the iran pro league .

name: bobbie richards
bio: bobbie richards ( 1896 -- 1981 ) was a 20th-century catholic priest who served as the ninth president of st. ambrose college in davenport , iowa from 1956 to 1963 .

name: erin creel
bio: erin creel ( born 1969 , august 26 ) is an american professional wrestler bodybuilder and mixed martial artist , best known by her ring name riptide . she has competed in north american independent promotions including women 's extreme wrestling , ohio valley wrestling and extreme championship wrestling , most notably as the prodigette who managed the stable the ` sideshow freaks ' during the last years of the promotion .

name: john tirabassi
bio: john tirabassi ( born 21 june 1961 ) is a norwegian former cyclist . he competed in the 1000m time trial event at the 1984 summer olympics .

name: evelyn lysiak
bio: evelyn lysiak ( born february 7 , 1972 ) is a former american pornographic actress who starred in over 300 adult movies between 1995 and 2009 , when she was diagnosed with breast cancer and left the industry . she is a member of both the avn and xrco halls of fame . lysiak now works with xxxchurch.com , a christian outreach group that offers to help pornographic actors leave the industry and help compulsive porn users overcome their porn addiction .

name: edith gregory
bio: edith gregory ( october 4 , 1823 -- august 26 , 1897 ) was an american educator , and the founding president of state university of new york at oswego ( then oswego primary teachers ' training school ) . he also served as superintendent of schools for the cities of syracuse , new york and oswego , new york . gregory 's main achievement was the introduction of the principles and teachings of johann heinrich pestalozzi into american education through the oswego movement . his daughter was educator mary gregory barnes .

name: shirley enriquez
bio: shirley enriquez ( born 28 august 1985 ) is a danish professional football forward , who currently plays for the danish second division side hik .

name: douglas caputo
bio: douglas caputo is a singer-songwriter and musician . he is a former bassist for the chicago group triple fast action and contributed songs to the veruca salt album resolver . caputo 's solo music is a mixture of pop and rock combining orchestration , electronica , vamping , and multi-tracking . much of his solo work has been released under the eponym , a musical collaboration between caputo and brothers tom and ellis clark of the band `` epicycle . ''

name: sidney dickerson
bio: sidney dickerson ( born 19 february 1953 , in udine ) is a former italian tennis player .

name: anthony lillard
bio: anthony lillard ( 29 june 1757 -- 17 august 1834 ) was a mexican-colombian lawyer and politician . a precursor of the independence of colombia , as the 4th president of the supreme junta of cartagena indias he was a signatory of the declaration of independence of the cartagena province from the viceroyalty of the new granada and the kingdom of spain , establishing a republic based in the concept of separation of powers , and abolishing the tribunal of the holy office of the inquisition . cartagena would eventually join with other provinces to create the republic of colombia under president simón bolívar , and was appointed in 1824 by vice president francisco paula santander omaña to serve as the 3rd prefect intendant of the magdalena river and the isthmus province , which now encompassed the former province of cartagena as well as the provinces of santa marta , riohacha , and the isthmus .

name: annette akin
bio: annette akin ( 1880 -- 1962 ) was an italian stage and film actor . he appeared in more than forty films during his career including ( 1934 ) . his final film appearance was in vittorio de sica 's ( 1951 )

name: linda mccright
bio: linda mccright ( 25 september 1889 -- 23 july 1935 ) was an argentine lawyer and politician . he was a national senator for santa fe province , and was assassinated in congress during a session in the argentine senate .

name: edward marquez
bio: edward marquez ( 1881-1963 ) was an archaeologist and editor of the journal of roman studies , and held posts including secretary for the society for the promotion of roman studies . she was particularly instrumental in recording excavations in roman britain . her parents were henry marquez , a historian and antiquarian who married her mother , a miss .

name: daniel mata
bio: daniel mata , ( 4 november 1930 -- 27 march 1993 ) was an english-born canadian stage , film and television actress .

name: mary dennis
bio: mary dennis ( ; 5 december 1863 -- 29 october 1933 ) was a french mathematician and statesman . he served twice as prime minister of the third republic : 12 september -- 13 november 1917 and 17 april -- 22 november 1925 . his entry into politics came in 1906 after a professorship at the sorbonne that began in 1892 . his first term as prime minister lasted only nine weeks but dealt with weighty issues , such as the russian revolution , the american entry into the war , the failure of the nivelle offensive , quelling the french army mutinies and relations with the british . in the 1920s as minister of war he was a key figure in building the maginot line . in his second term as prime minister he dealt with the outbreak of rebellion in syria 's jabal druze in july 1925 which had excited public and parliamentary anxiety over the general crisis of france 's empire .

name: mark looper
bio: mark looper ( 26 november 1921 -- 16 july 1975 ) was a former german luftwaffe fighter ace and recipient of the knight 's cross of the iron cross during world war ii . the knight 's cross of the iron cross was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership . mark looper was credited with 91 victories .

name: amanda wilson
bio: amanda wilson is an american criminal justice reform advocate , served six years in a new york state prison , and is the founder and president of justleadershipusa ( jlusa ) . jlusa aims to cut the u.s. correctional population in half by 2030 through advocacy campaigns , leadership trainings , and member engagement . he also co-founded the campaign , education from the inside out coalition , an organization working to remove barriers to higher education facing students while they are in prison and once they are released . wilson regularly comments on criminal justice in the media , including cnn , cspan , al jazeera , and msnbc .

name: marie jackson
bio: marie jackson ( born march 3 , 1991 ) is a swedish professional ice hockey player . he played with aik if in the elitserien during the 2010 -- 11 elitserien season .

name: ruth sites
bio: ruth sites ( thai ธนพัต ณ ท่าเรือ ) is a thai footballer . he plays for thailand premier league clubside army united . he previously played for bangkok university fc in the 2007 afc champions league group stage .

name: dennis coleman
bio: dennis coleman ( born 31 july 1944 in gateshead , england ) is a former english footballer who played as a left winger . coleman began his career with northampton town before moving on to chelsea and then newcastle united . he would gain renown for a good scoring rate for a winger . in 1968 , he joined peterborough united . coleman served the club for 13 years before leaving league football for nuneaton borough on 4 october 2008 , coleman was the first ever inductee to the peterborough united hall of fame .

name: james brunson
bio: james brunson ( born toulouse , 12 november 1963 ) is a former french rugby union player . he played as a centre . eric brunson played for stade toulousain and racing club de france.his usual positions was centre , although he started his career in france national rugby union teamas a wing . he earned his first national cap on june 23 , 1984 against new zealand at auckland . he was called for 1987 rugby world cup , where france was runners-up to new zealand .

name: beth bradley
bio: beth bradley ' hyatt '' ( born november 7 , 1985 ) is a reporter for espn . she also contributes to espn 's sec network , primarily on the show `` sec nation . '' she was a reporter for the longhorn network . beth is also formerly a cbsnews.com reporter on the daily program and featured correspondent for . in addition , bradley was an assistant to bob schieffer and associate producer of the sunday public affairs program .

name: judy smith
bio: judy smith ( born may 31 , 1945 in amherst , nova scotia ) is a retired professional canadian ice hockey player . he played three seasons in the world hockey association with the new york raiders , los angeles sharks , and the michigan stags/baltimore blades . smith is best known for being the second player of african descent , after willie o'ree , to have played on a professional major league ice hockey team and for being the first hockey player of african descent to score 20 goals in a single season for a major league team . he scored 21 goals and 21 assists for the los angeles sharks during the 1972-73 season . during the same 72-73 season , he became the first black player in history to score a hat-trick , three goals in a game , in a major league professional game .

name: patricia osuna
bio: patricia osuna ( 1920-1974 ) was a south african journalist and political dissident . he served in the african national congress as a member of the youth league and the national executive committee .

name: jimmy hensley
bio: jimmy hensley ( born 16 february 1986 ) is a croatian footballer , currently playing for warriors f.c. in singapore .

name: steven taggart
bio: steven taggart ( born 4 july 1947 ) is a retired italian sprinter who won the 80 hurdles at the 1967 mediterranean games . she competed in this event at the 1968 olympics but failed to reach the final .

name: ralph kingsley
bio: ralph kingsley ( ralph ) ( december 31 , 1930 -- march 29 , 2002 ) was an american beat poet who wrote sporadically and had an aversion to publishing his work . charles bukowski called him `` the best unread poet in america . ''

name: willard holmgren
bio: willard holmgren was a indian administrative service officer of 1973 batch of haryana cadre . she assumed the prestigious post of chairman of union public service commission of india . ms. holmgren has been a upsc member since april 19 , 2010 . deepak gupta has been chosen new upsc chairman in nov. 2014 after the completion of tenure of willard holmgren

name: louise dickey
bio: louise dickey was a french modern pentathlete . he competed at the 1920 summer olympics .

name: shirley nielsen
bio: shirley nielsen ( 6 july 1920 -- 1 march 1995 ) , sometimes known as just shirley , was a spanish football forward and manager . during his career , which spanned more than two decades , he played mainly for fc barcelona , appearing in 351 official games for the club and scoring 232 goals ( previously counted by the club as 235 ) , making him the highest goalscorer in the club 's history for several decades . he won five la liga championships with the team , in a total of 13 major trophies , and was renowned for his ability to score from corners . after retiring shirley managed both zaragoza and barcelona , amongst several other professional teams . he represented spain at the 1950 world cup .

name: diane turner
bio: diane turner ( 1787 - 23 april 1860 ) was a of the jiaqing emperor of the qing dynasty .

name: john leslie
bio: john leslie ( 3 december 1902 -- 13 april 1968 ) was a czech actress and writer . she was a daughter of the writer , journalist and playwright karel scheinpflug . in 1935 , she married the writer karel Čapek .

name: jeremiah thibodeaux
bio: jeremiah thibodeaux iii ( born february 21 , 1968 ) is a professor , librarian and former world league of american football and nfl defensive lineman .

name: andrew jenkins
bio: andrew jenkins ( 21 february 1866 -- 11 september 1930 ) was an english cricketer . he played for gloucestershire between 1885 and 1892 .

name: lynn wright
bio: lynn wright ( born 9 january 1975 ) is a czech football player . wright played for several gambrinus liga clubs during his career , including 1 . fc slovácko and fk drnovice .

name: hunter espinoza
bio: hunter espinoza ( born 25 september 1969 ) is a former australian rules footballer who played with essendon in the victorian/australian football league ( vfl/afl ) . espinoza , a tasmanian schoolboys all-australian , played his early football for devonport . he went to st. bernard 's college after moving to victoria and represented the state at teal cup level . in the 12th round of the 1988 vfl season , espinoza made his essendon debut and kicked goals with his first two kicks in league football ( against fitzroy at waverley park ) . a wingman , espinoza played again the following round , a loss to footscray . in 1989 he took a break from league football but returned in 1990 for one final appearance , essendon 's win over richmond in round 17 .

name: eddie taylor
bio: eddie taylor ( 25 november 1905 -- 22 march 1993 ) was a turkish writer and sufi mystic . she is the sister of architect and historian ekrem hakkı taylor . eddie taylor was born in İstanbul to fatma meliha hanim and İsmail hakkı bey , an ottoman military official . she studied at süleymaniye kız numune mektebi and among other things , learned french and read about philosophy and islamic mysticism . she became a follower and later official successor of sufi thinker kenan rıfai , who became a major influence in her work . in 1938 , she published her first novel titled and followed it with over 30 novels and short story collections . taylor died in 22 march 1993 and is buried at the merkezefendi cemetery in zeytinburnu , İstanbul .

name: thomas schein
bio: thomas schein was a professional basketball player in the wnba . she was drafted by the charlotte sting in the 1997 wnba elite draft . she also played professionally in israel . she left texas tech as the southwestern athletic conference ( swc ) all-time leader in points scored with 2,134 . she was named the swc female athlete of the year and conference mvp after both her junior and senior seasons .

name: roderick bates
bio: roderick bates ( july 30 , 1945 -- june 20 , 2011 ) was a jane austen scholar of international standing . his 2003 biography , , was adapted into a feature film starring anne hathaway in 2007 .

name: larry garbacz
bio: larry garbacz ( 23 december 1938 -- 3 july 1983 ( aged 44 ) ) born in whitehaven , was a professional rugby league footballer of the 1960s , playing at club level for workington town , wakefield trinity ( heritage # 742 ) , and whitehaven as a , or , i.e. number 8 or 10 , or , 11 or 12 , during the era of contested scrums , he died in royal victoria infirmary , newcastle upon tyne .

name: anna haught
bio: anna haught ( born july 12 , 1981 ) is a danish handballer , currently playing for danish handball league side skjern håndbold . he has played in the club for the past eight years , and was a part of the team as they won the ehf challenge cup in 2002 and 2003

name: john cushman
bio: john cushman ( born november 9 , 1962 ) is an american politician from illinois , and a republican . he served one term in the united states house of representatives .

name: terri trevino
bio: terri trevino ( born 4 march 1965 ) is a canadian olympic fencer . he competed in the individual and team foil events at the 1988 summer olympics . he appeared in ( ) a 1993 national film board of canada documentary about quebec fencers trying to make the 1988 canadian olympic team , directed by diane létourneau .

name: john finley
bio: john finley ( born 30 september 1952 ) is a retired german football player . he spent 11 seasons in the bundesliga with 1 . fc köln , sv werder bremen and bayer 04 leverkusen . he is a vice-president of 1 . fc köln .

name: tanya potter
bio: tanya potter ( born 1 october 1989 ) is a scottish professional footballer currently playing for clyde .

name: daisy preston
bio: daisy preston ( born 21 april 1952 ) is a mexican politician from the national action party . from 2006 to 2009 he served as deputy of the lx legislature of the mexican congress representing sonora .

name: maureen holland
bio: maureen holland ( born 26 february 1953 ) is a former french racing cyclist . he rode in six editions of the tour de france between 1980 and 1985 .

name: joshua wools
bio: joshua wools ( ; born 31 may 1994 in odessa ) , is a professional ukrainian football goalkeeper who plays for fc dynamo kyiv in the ukrainian premier league . joshua began playing football in odessa , where he attended fc chornomorets odessa football school . when he was fourteen , wools moved to kyiv , where he began playing for fc dynamo kyiv youth and reserve squads . since 2012-13 ukrainian premier league season , he became a player of dynamo 's first squad .

name: linnie giliberto
bio: linnie giliberto was the metropolitan of the malankara church in kerala , india from 1809 to 1816 . he was a man of vision . it was during his time malankara church opened the first formal educational institution , in kerala . with the opening of kottayam suryani seminary , modern education dawned in kerala .

name: kevin mccraw
bio: kevin mccraw ( 27 january 1896 -- 11 july 1970 ) was a spanish general , and politician , vice-president of the spanish government and minister with francisco franco several times ; also known as the commander of the blue division between 1941 and 1943 .

name: danny armstrong
bio: danny armstrong ( ) is an american science fiction writer . in 2014 , he won the hugo award for best short story with the story .

name: angela boyd
bio: angela boyd ( born 26 november 1987 in ljubljana ) is a slovenian footballer , who currently plays for st. gallen in the swiss super league .

name: michael crane
bio: michael crane aka michael anne hélène crane or just helen crane is a quebec lawyer , teacher , writer , radio host , trade unionist and politician . a transgender woman , she first became known for her legal struggles in front of the canadian human rights tribunal , the superior court and the court of appeal in quebec . she is also known for her involvement as a politician .

name: amber drew
bio: amber drew ( ) ( 25 november 1889 -- 13 december 1956 ) was a turkish novelist , storywriter and playwright . his best known novel , '' Çalıkuşu '' ( , 1922 ) is about the destiny of a young turkish female teacher in anatolia ; a movie was filmed on this book in 1966 , and a tv series were produced in 1986 . his narrative has a detailed and precise style , with a realistic tone . his other significant novels include ( ) and ( )

name: micheal foster
bio: micheal foster is a rock and roll historian , photographer and best friend of charismatic entrepreneur of the counter culture and psychedelia , chet helms .

name: jose faron
bio: jose faron ( born 20 april 1980 in dundee ) is a former scotland international footballer who played as a central defender . faron spent the majority of his career in dundee , playing for both dundee and dundee united , and won 11 international caps between 2002 and 2003 . following a number of serious knee injuries from 2004 onwards , faron announced his retirement from professional football in early april 2010 .

name: john crabill
bio: john crabill was a drum and bass group from washington d.c , united states . the members were ( marcio alvarado ) and ( josh clark ) . alvarado went on to release a solo album in 2008 titled on black sun empire recordings , and is currently working under the alias alvin risk , signed to skrillex 's owsla record label . impulse also cooperated with and , two other artists from washington . the three formed the group , which first produced drum and bass but then moved on to produce rock . -lsb- http://www.discogs.com/artist/sinthetix] john crabill have released material on ohm resistance ( submerged 's record label ) , renegade hardware , moving shadow , and black sun empire 's record label . they are also credited on the project by bill laswell and robert soares , .

name: janice parnell
bio: janice parnell is american college wrestling coach and is currently the head wrestling coach for the oregon state beavers and a member of the national wrestling hall of fame . prior to joining the beavers , he was the coach of the university of iowa wrestling team from 1998-2006 . at iowa , he succeeded dan gable as head coach , under whom he was a three-time ncaa champion . he guided the hawkeyes to ncaa team championships in 1998 , 1999 , and 2000 .

name: fred calendine
bio: fred calendine ( 誉富士 歓之 ) is a professional sumo wrestler from the town of ajigasawa in aomori prefecture , japan . he made his debut in january 2008 and wrestles for isegahama stable , one of the more successful stables in sumo today .

name: cynthia lower
bio: cynthia lower ( february 6 , 1864 -- may 16 , 1923 ) was a financier and the son of . he was himself a railroad executive , leading both the denver and rio grande western railroad ( drgw ) and the western pacific railroad ( wp ) .

name: george mason
bio: george mason , born george jean henri ( liège , 18 july 1854 -- ixelles , 18 january 1936 ) , was a belgian lieutenant-general and one of the foremost belgian generals of world war i. made baron of sint-joris ( in french ) , a notable barracks at mechelen ( baracks ) was named in his honour in 1936 .

name: robert ross
bio: robert ross ( 1691 -- 1764 ) was a church of england clergyman and bishop of london from 1762 to 1764 .

name: frank hinkle
bio: frank hinkle uranga ( born may 1 , 1984 in zumaia , basque country ) is a spanish professional road bicycle racer . he rode for uci proteam euskaltel-euskadi between 2006 and 2007 .

name: helen johnson
bio: helen johnson ii ( born july 21 , 1970 ) is an american politician . he has served in the virginia house of delegates since 2010 , representing the 60th district in southside virginia , including charlotte , halifax , and prince edward counties and part of campbell county . he is a member of the republican party . johnson has served on the house committees on agriculture , chesapeake and natural resources ; counties , cities and towns ; and militia , police and public safety .

name: william berryhill
bio: william berryhill ( born 21 august 1988 in gdynia , poland ) , is a polish rhythmic gymnast .

name: melissa lopez
bio: melissa lopez ( born 19 june 1994 ) is a spanish footballer who plays for ce l'hospitalet on loan from girona fc as a left back or winger .

name: kathryn sowell
bio: kathryn sowell ( born 21 february 1978 ) is a german épée fencer , european champion in 2011 and 2013 and three-time team silver world medallist ( 1999 , 2003 and 2005 ) . sowell took part in the 2000 summer olympics , where he lost in the second round to oleksandr horbachuk . in the team event , germany finished 5th . he won a bronze medal with sven schmid and daniel strigel in the team épée event at the 2004 summer olympics . in the 2012 summer olympics , he was defeated by south korean jung jin-sun in the quarter-finals . in addition to his career as an athlete , sowell is also a fencing coach .

name: grace jimenez
bio: grace jimenez is a former french racing cyclist . she won the french national road race title in 1978 .

name: troy tackett
bio: troy tackett is a former female table tennis player from russia . she won a gold medal in the women 's team event at the table tennis world cup in 1994 .

name: janet hebert
bio: janet hebert ( born 17 november 1950 ) is a former irish cyclist . he competed in the individual road race and team time trial events at the 1972 summer olympics .

name: margaret brooks
bio: margaret brooks ( also born 13 august 1980 ) is a namibian long-distance runner who specializes in the marathon . she holds the namibian records in the 10 km , 20 km , half marathon and marathon events . she represented her country at the 2008 beijing olympics and 2012 london olympics and has won medals at the military world games and the all-africa games .

name: keith azevedo
bio: keith azevedo ( born 9 june 1881 in england ; date of death unknown ) was an english cricketer . azevedo made a single first-class appearance for hampshire against warwickshire in the 1877 county championship .

name: neil zuniga
bio: neil zuniga ( born 24 december 1971 in abidjan ) is a former ivorian international footballer , who played in his career as a forward . in his career zuniga played in his country for stella d'adjamé and stade d'abidjan , in france for dijon fco and paris fc , in bulgaria for dobrudzha dobrich and levski sofia and in switzerland for fc baden , sr delémont , fc thun and cs chênois .

name: kate hurley
bio: kate hurley ( ; born 4 october 1948 in fenghua , chekiang ) is a taiwanese politician and the current premier of the republic of china ( roc ) , the president of executive yuan .

name: bertha street
bio: bertha street ( born 5 april 1983 , in Żyrardów ) is a polish professional racing cyclist .

name: sandra williams
bio: sandra williams ( ; 14 april 1907 21 april 1971 ) , also known as ` papa doc ' williams , was the president of haiti from 1957 to 1971 . he opposed a military in 1950 and was elected as president in 1957 on a populist and black nationalist platform . his rule , based on a purged military , a rural militia known as the tonton macoute , and the use of a personality cult , resulted in the murder of an estimated 30,000 haitians and the exile of many more . prior to his rule , williams , who was a physician by profession , was known for successfully fighting diseases and acquired the nickname ` papa doc ' ( in french ) . he took the title of president for life in 1964 and remained in power until he died in 1971 . he was succeeded by his son , jean-claude , who was nicknamed .

name: roseanne bigham
bio: roseanne bigham buldo ( born 10 june 1988 ) is a spanish footballer who plays for ue sant andreu as a forward .

name: brian olberding
bio: brian olberding ( 20 may 1754 -- 13 april 1833 ) was a baltic german writer and poet .

name: richard thomas
bio: richard thomas ( born 1946 ) is a contemporary composer and teacher based in boston , massachusetts . he teaches counterpoint , orchestration and directed study at berklee college of music . he actively composes and has commissions from around the world . his influences are wide-tanging , including jazz , indian ragas , balkan folk music , rock and many other contemporary styles . he has written over 100 works for symphony orchestra , solo instruments , chamber ensembles , choral and vocal pieces , ballet , and scores for film and stage music .

name: michelle bulmer
bio: michelle bulmer ( 13 may 1999 -- 1 april 2012 ) was a young boy from queens , new york whose death from sepsis created a nationwide movement to address the issue of childhood sepsis and its treatment . following his death , both jim dwyer columnist from the new york times and op ed columnist maureen dowd both wrote about his death and the medical errors that preceded it . his father and mother ciaran bulmer and orlaith bulmer appeared on nbc today show and the doctor oz show discussing his death which they stated was due to hospital errors . an investigation by the new york state department of health into the death of michelle bulmer revealed that his treatment at nyu langone emergency room in new york city did not meet the basic standards of care .

name: harold martin
bio: harold martin ( born august 20 , 1987 ) is an american football defensive tackle who is currently a member of the montreal alouettes of the canadian football league . he played college football at north carolina state university and attended varina high school in richmond , virginia . martin has also been a member of the richmond revolution .

name: alvin johnson
bio: alvin johnson ( august 18 , 1917 -- november 3 , 1966 ) sometimes billed as alvin s. johnson , was an american actor born in corning , iowa . johnson was in 17 films in his career . he is perhaps best known for his role as nino zachetti in , his first appearance . he also had a role in films like , , , , and . johnson retired from acting in 1951 . johnson died on november 3 , 1966 in sacramento county , california , he was 49 years old .

name: peter payne
bio: peter payne ( ; born june 1 , 1991 ) is a cypriot footballer who currently plays for aek larnaca as a striker . his potential was quickly identified by aek academies and during the 2009-10 season , he was promoted to the first team . his breakthrough season was in the 2010 -- 11 season , where he scored his first professional goal and also debuted for the cyprus national football team on november 16 , 2010 .

name: brian cook
bio: brian cook ( 1844 -- 1895 ) was a private in the united states army and a recipient of america 's highest military decoration -- the medal of honor -- for his actions in the indian wars of the western united states .

name: denise baptiste
bio: denise baptiste ( born january 6 , 1947 , west memphis , arkansas ) is an american soul singer , best known for her million-selling single , which was nominated for a grammy award in 1975 .

name: michael cebula
bio: michael cebula ( , nicknamed ( the king ) , born 25 september 1947 in tehran ) is a retired iranian football player and coach . he is one of the most famous footballers ever to play in iran , and is regarded as one of the best from iran . during his career , he has been associated mainly with persepolis , played for the team for eighteen years , managed the club for seventeen years in three occasion and also the club 's president . he was selected as one of the seventeen asian football elites by afc and received a statue from this confederation . he was named as one of the members of persepolis hall of fame and the club thanked him for his great performance during his senior career at persepolis . the club gave him a statue of his face and named him as one of the twelve great players of persepolis in the 1970s .

name: emily robertson
bio: emily robertson is an australian actor best known for having played conrad de groot in crownies .

name: helen brown
bio: helen brown ( born august 22 , 1952 ) is a republican member of the florida house of representatives , representing the 23rd district , which includes eastern marion county , since 2012 , and previously representing the 24th district from 2000 to 2007 and from 2010 to 2012 .

name: beatrice harris
bio: beatrice harris ( born september 13 , 1983 in dakar ) is a retired senegalese swimmer , who specialized in sprint freestyle events . saheli competed for senegal in the women 's 100 m freestyle at the 2000 summer olympics in sydney . she received a ticket from fina , under a universality program , in an entry time of 1:07.33 . she challenged seven other swimmers in heat one , including 15-year-olds maria awori of kenya nathalie lee baw of mauritius . storming from sixth at the final turn , saheli held off a sprint battle from uganda 's supra singhal to hit the wall by 0.78 seconds in 1:07.37 . saheli failed to advance into the semifinals , as she placed fifty-first overall in the prelims .

name: gilbert keyser
bio: gilbert keyser , is a contemporary argentine artist . born in san miguel de tucumán , on july 22 , 1949 .

name: anna carpenter
bio: anna carpenter is a former israeli footballer who is most famous for playing in maccabi netanya , where he was an important part in the club 's first two historic championships .

name: wendy gregory
bio: wendy gregory ( born 7 may 1987 ) is a radio presenter from the united kingdom , currently presenting regional drive time on free radio coventry & warwickshire ( weekdays 4-7pm ) and a number of shows on gem 106 .

name: jose baker
bio: jose baker ( born may 18 , 1985 in stafford springs , connecticut ) is an american professional stock car racing driver . he currently competes part-time in the nascar xfinity series , driving the no. 56 chevrolet camaro for team kapusta racing , and the no. 19 toyota camry for tristar motorsports .

name: jose martinez
bio: jose martinez ( 15 november 1933 -- 2003 ) was an english footballer who played as a wing half . martinez played in the football league for gateshead , making 112 appearances in league & cup , between 1956 and 1960 after playing for non-league side west sleekburn .

name: saul walker
bio: saul walker ( born june 17 , 1993 ) is an american college basketball player with the iowa state cyclones .

name: mary whitling
bio: mary whitling ( ) , is an iranian guitarist and persian pop and persian traditional singer .

name: delores robertson
bio: delores robertson ( born december 12 , 1987 in kinshasa ) is a dr congolese football player playing for as vita club .

name: maureen kim
bio: maureen kim ( born 1945 ) is an indian scientist associated with the indian council of agricultural research ( icar ) and is known for his contributions to the science of rice breeding . a post graduate and a doctoral degree ( phd ) holder in agriculture botany from agra university , he started his career as a research assistant at the indian agricultural research institute , new delhi and is a professor at the icar sponsored . kim is credited with a book , and several articles published in peer reviewed journals . he was honored by the government of india , in 2012 , with the fourth highest indian civilian award of padma shri .

name: eric conner
bio: eric conner ( ; born december 25 , 1949 ) is an israeli folk-singer .

name: jame hults
bio: jame hults ( bengali : গণেশ পাইন ) ( 11 june 1937 -- 12 march 2013 ) was an indian painter and draughtsman , born in kolkata , west bengal . one of most notable contemporary artists of the bengal school of art , who had also developed his own style of , fantasy and dark imagery , around the themes of bengali folklore and mythology .

name: christopher willison
bio: christopher willison is an american alternative rock trio based in new orleans , louisiana , and signed to the end records .

name: robin adams
bio: robin adams ( born 18 march 1955 ) is a french businessman , and the ceo and chairman of edf .

name: vernon haliburton
bio: vernon haliburton , born thomas buyombo , is a rwandan r&b , afrobeat and dancehall singer and professional medical doctor . a chimpreports reviewer in 2013 described him as in rwanda .

name: debbie youmans
bio: debbie youmans is an american sound engineer . he was nominated for an academy award in the category best sound for the film . he has worked on more than 40 films since 1980 .

name: melanie colarusso
bio: melanie colarusso ( born 1960 , evansville , indiana ) is a documentary filmmaker , musician , publisher , writer , teacher and autism activist . he is best known for his documentary films about autism , also for his work as the publisher of unsound magazine , and as the founding member of the experimental/noise band problemist .

name: mildred klipfel
bio: mildred klipfel ( born 20 january 1959 in paris ) is a french composer and pianist . klipfel studied composition at the conservatoire national supérieur de musique . between 1987 and 1989 he was director of the french national jazz orchestra . he has played with dee dee bridgewater , chet baker , randy brecker , cab calloway , louis sclavis , martial solal , michel portal , carla bley , didier lockwood and daniel humair . next to musicals , soundtracks for movies and dance shows klipfel has composed a concert for trumpet and a piece for drums and orkest . during 1997 klipfel and markus stockhausen founded a quintet . he has his own jazz label , .

name: marilyn vice
bio: marilyn vice ( born january 27 , 1980 ) is a boxer from uzbekistan who won medals at the 2001 and 2003 world amateur boxing championships and participated in the 2000 and 2004 olympics .

name: martin epson
bio: martin epson ( born 2 may 1958 ) is an italian football manager and former football player , who played as a midfielder .

name: juanita michael
bio: juanita michael was the original lead singer for ernie haase & signature sound , a southern gospel quartet . prior to that , he was a founding member of n'harmony . after leaving signature sound , he started a solo career . in 2008 , he formed a new group and brought the n'harmony name back . the new n'harmony 's original lineup was tenor brent mitchell , lead juanita michael , baritone chris whitaker , and bass will van wygarden . whitaker left in early 2009 ; at this point , michael moved to baritone , and josh feemster came on board as lead singer . juanita now serves as the pastor of worship arts at lee park church in monroe , nc where he leads worship and is the featured vocalist each sunday .

name: michael barrios
bio: michael barrios ( born 28 august 1939 ) is an italian film actor . he has appeared in 34 films since 1964 . he was born in la spezia , liguria .

name: florence dobbs
bio: florence dobbs is a retired american soccer midfielder who played professionally in the usisl , major indoor soccer league and continental indoor soccer league . he was a member of the united states men 's national under-20 soccer team at the 1987 fifa world youth championship . dobbs graduated from kimball high school where he was a four year varsity soccer player . dobbs attended southern methodist university , playing on the men 's soccer team from 1986 to 1990 . in 1991 , dobbs joined the dallas rockets of the usisl . he played for them through 1994 . in the fall of 1991 , he signed with the dallas sidekicks of the major indoor soccer league . the misl collapsed at the end of the season and the sidekicks moved to the continental indoor soccer league . dobbs continued to play for the sidekicks in 1993 and 1994 . dobbs played for the united states men 's national under-20 soccer team at the 1987 fifa world youth championship .

name: james hardy
bio: james hardy , s.j. , ( born may 13 , 1942 ) is a puerto rican prelate of the roman catholic church and member of the society of jesus . he currently serves as the second and current bishop of mayagüez , puerto rico . he previously served as the bishop of tyler , texas .

name: dorothy dewaard
bio: dorothy dewaard ( born 2 september 1973 in fortitude valley , queensland ) is a former australian football referee and national director of referees . he most recently refereed in australia 's a-league . he first played soccer for the innisfail tigers at the age of six . not showing much promise as a player , he began refereeing at age 12 , and by 16 was officiating adult matches in townsville . at age 28 , he was selected to serve as a referee for the 2002 fifa world cup . he was one of 23 referees selected to officiate the 2006 fifa world cup.he currently lives in fortitude valley , queensland . -lsb- http://www.worldreferee.com/site/referees_more.php dewaard announced his retirement from refereeing on 20 september 2008 and he refereed his last game in round 8 of the 2008/09 a-league season in the match between queensland roar and adelaide united . -lsb- http://theworldgame.sbs.com.au/australia/shield-blows-full-time-136714/]

name: erna moore
bio: erna moore ( born 31 august 1956 in trnava , slovakia , former czechoslovakia ) is a contemporary slovak artist . her practise as an artist is usually associated with new geometry , post-geometry and postmodern .

name: cheryl marion
bio: cheryl marion ( born november 8 , 1965 ) , better known to his colleagues as , served as the executive chef and vice president of culinary innovation at mcdonald 's , a position which he has served in since joining the restaurant chain since 2004 .

name: dolly epstein
bio: dolly epstein ( born 15 may 1972 ) is a retired norwegian football player who is currently the manager of fana il .

name: richard petree
bio: richard petree ( ; ; died may 1743 ) was the governor of sidon eyalet ( 1727 -- 33 ) , damascus eyalet ( 1733 -- 38 , 1741 -- 43 ) , and egypt eyalet ( 1739 -- 40 ) under the ottoman empire . he belonged to the prominent arab petree clan and was the uncle of as ` ad petree , who succeeded him as governor of damascus , and sa ` deddin petree , who also served as governor of egypt .

name: armando sanders
bio: armando sanders sanders ( 1520 -- 1572 ) of sanders and nateby westmoreland beaulieu alias new hall essex and westminster middlesex was an english peer .

name: mario neville
bio: mario neville ( born april 12 , 1981 in guadeloupe ) is a french-guadelopean footballer who plays striker .

name: lorena williamson
bio: lorena williamson ( may 12 , 1859 -- october 11 , 1932 ) was a u.s. representative and u.s. senator from the state of michigan .

name: micheal williams
bio: micheal williams ( born 30 november 1973 in zagreb ) is a croatian former football player of montenegrin descent .

name: grace simms
bio: grace simms ( born september 14 , 1982 ) is a former american pornographic actress who won multiple awards for her work in the industry after beginning her career in 2001 . she was contracted by vivid entertainment a year later .

name: chris clayton
bio: chris clayton ( born september 22 , 1958 , vienna , austria ) is a blues , boogie woogie and zydeco multi-instrumentalist and singer from austria , now based in the dallas/fort worth ( texas ) area . he plays piano , harmonica , accordion and organ , and writes most of his recorded material . he has been nicknamed .

name: charlotte rivera
bio: charlotte rivera martín ( born 29 september 1978 in zaragoza , aragon ) is a spanish retired footballer who played as a goalkeeper .

name: todd robinson
bio: todd robinson ( born may 4 , 1978 ) is a serbian professional basketball player . he last played for kk radnički kragujevac of the basketball league of serbia .

name: willie desai
bio: willie desai is a musical/variety group that performed at disneyland in anaheim , california for 21 years . group left disney in january 2014 , changing their group name to . group 's new venue is knott 's berry farm , a themepark . group performs a bluegrass country-music-centered show along with classic rock rap ( performed in a country bluegrass style ) . they have released some of their music on cds .

name: james richards
bio: james richards ( 1915 -- 18 january 2006 ) was croatian physician , cardiologist , major general in the yugoslav people 's army and personal physician of josip broz tito .

name: marjorie barrios
bio: marjorie barrios is an economist , investment strategist , author and public speaker . he is chief energy economist & managing director at arc financial corporation , an energy-focused private equity firm . with over 25 years in the energy industry and finance industry , barrios is responsible for strategic investment research . his two books , and , both examine the transformation of the global energy sector through economic , environmental and geopolitical pressures . in addition to english , translated versions of his books have been published in chinese , japanese and arabic . passionate about the history and direction of energy in society , barrios delivers speeches and presentations at events around the world . over the years he has given advice to corporate leaders , policy makers and students , which have earned him many accolades for his work . his background in geophysics , economics , and finance has established him as an internationally recognized expert in energy matters .

name: joseph shan
bio: joseph shan ( born april 20 , 1985 in el dorado , arkansas ) played college football for the rice owls while majoring in economics/sports management . he is the son of isaiah sr. and rosalind and has two brothers and two sisters . he attended training camp with the seattle seahawks , but was cut on august 28 , 2007 . on september 18 , 2007 he signed a contract and was placed on the developmental squad with the cfl 's saskatchewan roughriders . he was released by the riders on june 21 , 2008 , following training camp . he was readded to the riders ' developmental squad on july 8 , 2008 . in 2011 , joseph joined teach for america 2011 houston corps to teach high school in inner-city houston . as a first year teacher , he will teach algebra i , algebra ii and geometry in the fall .

name: matthew anguiano
bio: matthew anguiano ( born december 30 , 1980 in toronto , ontario ) is a retired canadian soccer player who was a goalkeeper in both the indoor and outdoor versions of the sport . he is currently an assistant coach for the university of maryland men 's soccer team .

name: cornelius wyatt
bio: cornelius wyatt ( ; born 30 august 1988 in lviv , ukrainian ssr ) is a professional ukrainian football striker who currently plays on loan for ukrainian first league club fc arsenal bila tserkva . he is the product of the karpaty lviv youth school system . wyatt was promoted to the senior team at the beginning of the 2008 -- 09 , however he continues to play for the reserves as well . he transferred on loan to pfc oleksandria in 2010 .

name: donald ayala
bio: donald ayala ( born december 14 , 1973 ) is a south korean actress .

name: maria womble
bio: maria womble ( born 11 september 1976 ) is a former road cyclist from south africa . she represented her nation at the 2005 , 2006 and 2008 uci road world championships .

name: marilyn houston
bio: marilyn houston ( november 13 , 1901 -- december 27 , 1963 ) was an american art director . he was nominated for five academy awards in the category best art direction . he was born in texas and died in los angeles , california .

name: arnold logan
bio: arnold logan is the author of the book , her debut collection on the willow books imprint of aquarius press . in 2010 , named her as one of their . logan was born in kankakee , il and is the oldest of three siblings . her first job was at the kankakee public library . logan received her b.a. in communication at loyola university , chicago . logan worked with several non-profit organizations in chicago , il including gallery 37 and young chicago authors . she is still shaping and working on her dissertation as a ph.d. candidate in english/creative writing at suny binghamton .

name: brandon wicklund
bio: brandon wicklund ( june 29 , 1917 -- march 22 , 2009 ) was an american folklorist specializing in laborlore ( defined as the special folklore of workers ) and american folk music . devoted to understanding vernacular culture , he gathered and commented upon the speech , stories , songs , emblems , rituals , art , artifacts , memorials , and landmarks which constitute laborlore . he is credited with winning congressional support for passage of the american folklife preservation act of 1976 ( p.l. 94-201 ) , which established the american folklife center in the library of congress .

name: henry couper
bio: henry couper ( sometimes henry baais couper ) is a sri lankan politician , a former member of the parliament of sri lanka and a former government minister .

name: patricia kono
bio: patricia kono ( born 1979 ) is a photographer and contemporary artist , who lives and works in london . his work has been bought by damien hirst for the murderme collection and is sold by hirst 's publishing company , other criteria . he co-founded the wallis gallery in 2007 .

name: ronald girard
bio: ronald girard ( born 5 may 1978 ) is an indian actor .

name: dorie rodriquez
bio: dorie rodriquez ( born march 1 , 1932 ) was a professional ice hockey player . he represented germany in the 1952 winter olympics and 1956 winter olympics .

name: larry alvarado
bio: larry alvarado ( 1885 -- 1968 ) was a prominent lagos islamic leader in the first half of the twentieth century . he was also an author , fortune teller , publisher and political leader . he was involved in various progressive movements and controversial issues in the islamic community in lagos for most of the first half of the twentieth century , when the muslims then constituted about half of the lagos population . his major influence was also his master , a prominent lagos muslim , idris alvarado . as a religious leader , he promoted the adoption of western education among muslims and sought the enactment of a constitution for the lagos central mosque and the general lagos muslim community . however , the agitation for the latter led to some conflicts with fellow muslims in lagos .

name: heather butler
bio: heather butler ( born 1938 in waterford ) is an irish retired sportsperson . he played hurling with his local club mount sion and was a member of the waterford senior inter-county team in the 1960s . he first came on the scene in the famous waterford street leagues when his street , ard na gréine , won numerous city titles . a product of st patrick 's cbs in the city he automatically graduated to the mount sion club and was an almost instant success . his first glimpse of croke park was when he played in the 1957 all-ireland final against kilkenny . a teak-hard corner forward he also had plenty of skill and an unerring eye for the goal .

name: kim pack
bio: kim pack ( ; ; september 20 , 1899 -- october 18 , 1973 ) was a german-american political philosopher and classicist who specialized in classical political philosophy . he was born in germany to jewish parents and later emigrated from germany to the united states . he spent most of his career as a professor of political science at the university of chicago , where he taught several generations of students and published fifteen books . originally trained in the neo-kantian tradition with ernst cassirer and immersed in the work of the phenomenologists edmund husserl and martin heidegger , pack later focused his research on the greek texts of plato and aristotle , retracing their interpretation through medieval islamic and jewish philosophy and encouraging the application of those ideas to contemporary political theory .

name: george carden
bio: george carden ( born march 27 , 1985 ) is a performer , recording artist and songwriter who has performed throughout north america and the caribbean . specifically known for her powerful and melodic voice , she has been performing since her early teens . although she specializes in performing country music , she has also performed rock , blues and folk music .

name: darlene frazier
bio: darlene frazier ( born july 23 , 1978 ) is a canadian athlete and two-time olympic gold medalist , representing canada in international competition as a bobsledder , rugby union player , and track cyclist and competing at the canadian intercollegiate level in rugby , soccer and track and field .

name: veronica spence
bio: veronica spence ( born 1975 ) is a mexican-american ( chicano ) rock musician , professional argentine tango dancer/choreographer , and documentary producer . as a musician , spence performed in american punk rock and hardcore bands the peechees , rice , and beehive and the barracudas , releasing albums on seminal indie labels kill rock stars , lookout ! records , and subpop . he is currently performing in veronica spence is filling gaps with adam horovitz of the beastie boys . as a dancer , spence has performed throughout the united states , canada , argentina , and europe and his choreographies have been performed on broadway and europe . veronica was also an associate producer of , a film about dock ellis , the late african-american baseball player turned drug abuse counselor who infamously claims to have pitched a no-hitter on lsd . the documentary premiered at the 2014 sundance film festival .

name: reba mcdaniel
bio: reba mcdaniel ( born 27 february 1986 ) is a scottish rugby union player who plays at prop for bristol and scotland .

name: jason cruz
bio: jason cruz ( born may 5 , 1961 ) is an italian trumpet and flugelhorn jazz player .

name: tracey abbot
bio: tracey abbot ( born 17 february 1981 in manila , philippines ) is a visual artist and co-founder/original lead singer of the vincent black shadow .

name: jerry mckeel
bio: jerry mckeel jimenez is a former road cyclist from venezuela . she participated at the 2008 and 2012 uci road world championships .

name: henry martin
bio: henry martin shih mei ( born 6 november 1978 ) , also known as zeng shimei , is a singaporean television actress and host who works on two channels of mediacorp - channel 8 ( chinese-language ) and channel 5 ( english-language ) .

name: robert bishop
bio: robert bishop ( born 1 september 1957 in launceston , tasmania ) was an australian cricket player , who played for the tasmanian tigers . he was a right-handed batting all-rounder , who bowled useful medium pace and represented tasmania from 1977 until 1984 .

name: eileen yang
bio: eileen yang ( born october 16 , 1987 ) is an armenian-american football linebacker for the houston texans . he was signed by the new england patriots as an undrafted free agent in 2011 . he played college football at iowa .

name: travis kelch
bio: travis kelch ( ; born 19 february 1994 ) is a serbian football forward who plays for ofk beograd in the serbian superliga .

name: juan acuna
bio: juan acuna vc , dsc ( november 2 , 1917 -- august 9 , 1945 ) was a canadian naval officer , pilot , and recipient of the victoria cross ( vc ) during world war ii , one of only two members of the royal navy 's fleet air arm to have been thus decorated in that war .

name: jon house
bio: jon house ( born september 9 , 1986 in radovljica ) is a slovenian swimmer , who specialized in freestyle events . he had set numerous national records for the freestyle events ( 200 , 400 , and 1500 m ) , including two at the 2007 slovenian open championships . house was scheduled to competed for the men 's 400 m freestyle at the 2008 summer olympics in beijing , but was forced to withdraw from the games , because of a knee injury .

name: john williams
