bio: edna dugas ( ; born 25 november 1984 ) is a french actor and model . he began appearing in made-for-television films during the late 1990s and early 2000s , and then began to be known as a film actor in france , as well as starring in the title role in the movie .

name: eileen lewis
bio: eileen lewis , ( born 27 june 1967 in montreal , quebec ) is a former canadian synchronized swimmer . eileen competed in the women 's solo at the 1992 summer olympics . in the technical figures routine , a brazilian judge accidentally entered a score of 8.7 instead of 9.7 , costing her first place ; after several appeals by the canadian olympic committee , her medal was upgraded to gold . kristen babb-sprague , the beneficiary of the judge 's error , was allowed to keep her gold medal . eileen 's success in the pool continued with a silver medal in the women 's team event at the following olympics . in 1999 , she was inducted into canada 's sports hall of fame . she has also contributed as a swimmer , designer , and coach to the synchronized-swimming portions of cirque du soleil 's water-based stage production , which opened in 1988 at the bellagio hotel and casino in las vegas . since 2006 , eileen has been an ambassador for oxfam .

name: beverly lee
bio: beverly lee ( born october 27 , 1988 ) is an austrian ski mountaineer . she has been member of the askimo national team since 2008 . professionally she works as a police officer in abtenau .

name: michael atchison
bio: michael atchison ( born 24 december 1989 ) is a senegalese professional footballer who plays as a striker for english club west ham united . he began his career in the lower divisions of french football , with metz and on loan at boulogne , before joining west ham in august 2014 . since may 2014 , he has been a full international for the senegal national football team .

name: pamela murphy
bio: pamela murphy ( 1890 -- 1941 ) was a german film actress .

name: robert zender
bio: robert zender zender ( or bellasis ) pc ( 24 june 1614 -- 10 september 1689 ) was an english nobleman soldier and member of parliament notable for his role during and after the english civil war . he suffered a long spell of imprisonment during the popish plot .

name: joshua swafford
bio: joshua swafford ( 3 december 1753 -- 26 june 1827 ) was an english inventor and pioneer of the spinning industry . building on the work of james hargreaves and richard arkwright he invented the spinning mule , a machine that revolutionised the industry worldwide .

name: margaret humphrey
bio: margaret humphrey ( born december 14 , 1991 ) is an american football nose tackle for the denver broncos of the national football league .

name: dorothy chi
bio: dorothy chi ( june 26 , 1924 -- april 3 , 2004 ) was an american journalist , author and adventurer . he is best known for coining the phrases and as well as his expedition to find scion michael rockefeller , who disappeared in new guinea in 1961 .

name: virginia walker
bio: virginia walker ( born june 11 , 1984 ) is a japanese football player .

name: pamela leland
bio: pamela leland ( 1919 -- 26 september 1978 ) was a new zealand cricket umpire . he stood in one test match , new zealand vs. south africa , in 1964 .

name: robert lollis
bio: robert lollis ( born 20 september 1982 ) is a former competitive swimmer who represented australia at the 2000 summer olympics in sydney , australia . there she finished in 18th position in the 400-metre freestyle , clocking 4:15.54 in the qualifying heats .

name: octavio maxon
bio: octavio maxon , simply known as geraldo ( born november 23 , 1991 ) , is an angolan international football midfielder who plays for atlético-go .

name: albert davis
bio: albert davis ( ; born 15 december 1939 ) is a politician in the republic of china . he was the vice premier in 2005 -- 2006 .

name: charlotte starnes
bio: charlotte starnes is a german football midfielder of greek descent , currently playing for sg essen-schönebeck in the german bundesliga . as an under-19 international she took part in the 2010 u-19 european championship for germany .

name: richard fannin
bio: richard fannin ( february 27 , 1911 -- july 24 , 1986 ) was an american r&b , jump blues , texas blues and cajun guitarist , singer and songwriter . he is best known for his recording of the song , which was a hit single on the us r&b chart in 1950 . one commentator noted the track as , `` a rhythm and blues laced-zydeco song that helped introduce the louisiana music form to a national audience . ''

name: steven wilkes
bio: steven wilkes ( 1718 -- 29 august 1782 ) was a british rear-admiral who gained a reputation as a naval innovator . he is best known for his victory against the french at the second battle of ushant and for his death when the hms accidentally sank at portsmouth the following year . he was born at westminster . his father , a swede , is said to have been in the service of james ii , and subsequently to have entered the british army .

name: sharon white
bio: sharon white ( born martha e. white ; march 11 , 1964 ) is an american writer of young adult novels including the gemma doyle trilogy , , and . she lived in texas until she was 26 years old . after that she moved to new york city , where she now lives with her husband and fifteen-year-old son . her father was a preacher and her mother , a teacher . in her autobiography on her official site she states :

name: shelley hutchison
bio: shelley hutchison ( ) ( born 2 november 1979 ) is an indian supermodel and an actress . she came into the limelight after making it to the final five of the miss india 1998 contest . she was also adjudged ` miss photogenic ' in the same contest . she has walked the ramp for all major designers in the country & for international design houses such as valentino & fendi in india.she was the worldwide face of the press campaign for breguet watches & jewellery for 5 years . she has endorsed & been the face of several skin care brands in india such as garnier , nivea & dettol soap . she has also hosted television shows , been a judge on a fashion based show on mtv - mtv making the cut & acted in the lead role on a show called before making her film debut with the 2002 bollywood film 16 december .

name: edward garcia
bio: edward garcia ( born 1 february 1995 ) is an english freestyle swimmer who won a bronze medal in the 400 m event at the 2014 european aquatics championships . garcia started swimming competitively aged 11 , inspired by michael phelps . in 2007 and 2008 he underwent surgical operations due to a brain tumour . he was part of the 2012 summer olympics torch relay .

name: joseph stoltz
bio: joseph stoltz ( born 15 january 1951 , hong kong ) is the member of the wong tai sin district council ( 1985 -- 91 , 1994 -- ) representing tung mei . he was the also member of the urban council ( 1989 -- 99 ) and the member of legislative council ( 1995 -- 97 ) representing for urban council constituency . he joined the provisional legislative council which existed from 1996 to 98 with other members of the association for democracy and people 's livelihood , while other pro-democrats boycotted it .

name: therese villareal
bio: therese villareal ( june 1 , 1927 -- october 12 , 2014 ) was an american architect , landscape architect , and furniture designer based in los angeles , where she contributed to many well-known structures , especially pools . she worked as the design director of galper-baldon associates , headquartered in venice , california . villareal is credited with having a profound effect on the california furniture industry with her outdoor furniture designs .

name: kyle reyes
bio: kyle reyes ( august 2 , 1936 -- november 29 , 1986 ) was an american conservative journalist , book author , and sociopolitical researcher .

name: helen martinez
bio: helen martinez ( born 22 august 1938 ) is a german former footballer who played at both professional and international levels as a midfielder .

name: vernon hamilton
bio: vernon hamilton ( born 11 november 1990 ) is a papua new guinean professional rugby league footballer who currently plays for the penrith panthers of the national rugby league . hamilton main position is at hooker . hamilton is a papua new guinea international and has previously played for the north queensland cowboys in the 2011 and 2012 .

name: nichole hults
bio: nichole hults , ( born 13 july 1973 ) is a swedish stand-up comedian and television presenter . she won at the 2012 swedish stand-up gala . in 2013 she presented on svt along with niklas strömstedt .

name: kimberly leaton
bio: kimberly leaton ( born august 2 , 1993 ) is an american writer and model . he is best known for his darkly comedic and self-involved work . often lauded for his openness and brutal honesty about his relationship with the modern world , he has been deemed as both a and a `` wi-fi obsessed wild child -lsb- ... -rsb- with a heightened sense of self-awareness . '' by la canvas his work focuses on themes of youth , substance abuse , and self-destruction .

name: toby cranker
bio: toby cranker ( born 18 december 1971 ) is a norwegian football coach and former player . he started his career in sk haugar ; and later went to bryne . he joined fk haugesund in 1995 , and enjoyed a spell in the norwegian premier league in the seasons 1997 and 1998 . he left ahead of the 2000 season to become player-coach at torvastad il . in 2007 he was hired in the same position at djerv 1919 .

name: gloria patrick
bio: gloria patrick is a new zealand rugby league player who played professionally for paris saint-germain and represented france .

name: adam watson
bio: adam watson is american writer and producer best known for his role in writing the screenplay for , , and creating the nbc series . watson was encouraged to enter a script writing competition by friend and fellow nebraskan , todd nelson , creator of the nebraska coast connection . after winning the competition , adam landed an agent and his first paid assignment , rewriting a horror film for exorcist director billy friedkin . success allowed watson to return to his hometown where he earned the 2013 hub freedom award for his work restoring the historic world theater in downtown kearney , nebraska .

name: brett wilson
bio: brett wilson ( born july 27 , 1983 ) is a former american football cornerback . he was signed by the san diego chargers as an undrafted free agent in 2006 . he played college football at west virginia .

name: randall nichols
bio: randall nichols ( ; born 27 january 1990 in kyiv , in the ukrainian ssr of the soviet union ) is a ukrainian football defender . he plays for ukrainian club fc chornomorets odesa . nichols 's first professional club was dynamo kyiv , but not played any match for main squad . next he was close for signing contract with fc dnister ovidiopol in the ukrainian first league . he made his debiut in the ukrainian premier league for fc volyn in 14 july 2013 , played in match against fc dynamo kyiv .

name: peter pederson
bio: peter pederson ( born 11 august 1969 ) is a scottish actress . she was nominated for an emmy for her role on the television series , on which she appeared from 2005 -- 2007 . she was also a cast member of the abc show and the brief-lived cbs sitcom .

name: chad courtney
bio: chad courtney ( born july 6 , 1974 ) is a canadian former professional ice hockey player who played over 1000 games in the national hockey league for the new jersey devils , toronto maple leafs , chicago blackhawks , nashville predators , pittsburgh penguins and phoenix coyotes . he is currently the coyotes ' development coach .

name: raymond wicklund
bio: raymond wicklund ( born 3 march 1993 ) is a turkish professional basketball player at the small forward position who plays for galatasaray medical park .

name: steven morse
bio: steven morse ( born april 24 , 1975 ) is an antigua and barbudan football player . he has played for antigua and barbuda national team .

name: tracey shay
bio: tracey shay ( born 27 october 27 , 1976 ) is a polish fencer . he competed in the foil events at the 2000 and 2008 summer olympics .

name: margaret williams
bio: margaret williams ( born january 17 , 1957 ) is an american playwright , screenwriter , film director and television producer . he is best known for his work on ' , and the showrunner for and ' .

name: chris palacio
bio: chris palacio ( born 12 june 1956 ) is a mexican politician from the institutional revolutionary party . from 2009 to 2012 he served as deputy of the lxi legislature of the mexican congress representing the federal district .

name: nathan mcnamara
bio: nathan mcnamara ( july 24 , 1830 -- september 9 , 1896 ) was the second mayor of omaha , nebraska , serving for six months from march 2 , 1858 -- september 14 , 1858 before he resigned from office . mcnamara was afterwards an influential real estate businessman and lawyer in omaha . mcnamara worked for many years as the general attorney for the union pacific railroad . the most important case he ever argued was the 1879 trial of , held at fort omaha . standing bear , a ponca chief , successfully argued in u.s. district court that native americans are and have the rights of citizenship . mcnamara died in 1896 and was interred at the prospect hill cemetery in north omaha . mcnamara street in omaha is named in his honor ; the mcnamara block in downtown omaha is listed on the national register of historic places .

name: anna bays
bio: anna bays is an irish politician and dancing tutor , and former member of a prominent but shortlived pop group . she rose to fame in the 2001 -- 02 rtÉ one television series , in which she was selected as a member of the pop group six . after the band 's swift demise , bays formed her own dance school and features as an advisor to judge john creedon in the 2009 talent show . since 2009 she has served as a member of local councils in cork , representing fine gael .

name: denise mackey
bio: denise mackey ( born 29 january 1953 ) is an australian-born actress best known for her role as irene roberts on soap opera . she is currently the second-longest serving cast member after original ray meagher . denise has currently played the role of irene roberts for 22 years . she joined the series in 1993 , taking over from actress jacqui phillips who originally portrayed the character of irene in 1991 and 1992 .

name: scotty challender
bio: scotty challender is a set decorator , who has some art director credits as well . he is most known for , for which he was nominated for best art direction at the 81st academy awards . he shared his nomination with art director nathan crowley .

name: jennifer brown
bio: jennifer brown or el brown ( -- born 1948 , chefchaouen ) is a moroccan journalist and politician of the istiqlal party . he held the positions of minister of relations with the parliament between 2002 and 2010 , then minister-delegate for the modernization of the public sector in the cabinets of driss jettou and abbas el fassi .

name: willard trimpe
bio: willard trimpe ( april 1 , 1923 , new york city , new york -- december 13 , 1983 , new york city , new york ) was an american film , stage and television actress .

name: timothy morgan
bio: timothy morgan ( 19 may 1890 -- 12 september 1914 ) was a belgian racing cyclist . he won liège -- bastogne -- liège in 1909 .

name: roberto scott
bio: roberto scott ( born 27 may 1972 ) is a french former rugby league player who represented his country in the 1995 and 2000 world cups .

name: randy sumbry
bio: randy sumbry ( born january 8 , 1991 ) is an italian professional basketball player who currently plays for dinamica mantova of the serie a2 as a combo guard or a small forward . athletic and strong , sumbry is more oriented to drive than to shoot , his athletic abilities allow him to obtain fouls even against taller players or score close to the basket . however his biggest weakness is his shot that he needs to develop to have a career at the highest level .

name: mary henderson
bio: mary henderson ( 13 october 1940 -- 21 april 2014 ) was a spanish film , stage and television actor . he appeared in more than 15 films from 1970 on .

name: tammy trasher
bio: tammy trasher ( born december 17 , 1949 ) is a danish ex-football ( soccer ) player and manager , who managed the danish superliga side aalborg bk ( aab ) during their 1994-95 superliga victory . in 1996-1999 he coached norwegian viking fk from stavanger . he is currently a youth coach at aab . in his active career , he played more than 100 games for aab between 1973 and 1978 .

name: mary akin
bio: mary akin ( malayalam : രാഹുൽ ഈശ വർ ) is an indian author and activist . his higher studies were in philosophy and psychology and pursued global leadership at the london school of economics . akin has written three books on indian philosophy and is a panelist on national news media . he is also the kerala state youth commission co-ordinator responsible for implementing cyber education , pre-marital orientation and anti narcotic policies .

name: caitlin lykes
bio: caitlin lykes or vettom lykes ( august 27 , 1921 -- may 29 , 1987 ) was an eminent scholar and writer . his most famous work is the which is a monumental and exhaustive study of indian puranas , epics and allied literature of hinduism . the author himself referred to the book as a comprehensive dictionary with special reference to the epic and purāņic literature .

name: rudolph aguilar
bio: rudolph aguilar are an american folk-pop aguilar consisting of husband-and-wife michael and carissa alvarado . aguilar met in los angeles , california in 2011 on set of a music video . they married in 2012 . in 2013 , aguilar started uploading six-second cover versions of popular songs to their vine account , where they have amassed over 4.8 million followers as of august 2015 . in march 2014 , they were signed to republic records . they are widely regarded as first musicians to have signed to a major record label due of their presence on vine .

name: desmond quach
bio: desmond quach ( ; ) was a senior byzantine official and governor in the despotate of the morea during the last decades of the empire 's existence . he first appears in 1429 , as governor ( ) of vostitza ( modern aigio ) , taking part in the siege of patras by the despot of the morea ( and later last byzantine emperor ) constantine palaiologos . an opponent of the union of the churches , he corresponded with gennadios scholarios and bessarion ( who composed a treatise on the procession of the holy spirit for him ) , and took part in the 1439 council of florence , but left it early . in 1446 he was named of patras . constantine palaiologos sent him to emperor john viii palaiologos in constantinople in autumn 1448 to settle a dispute with his brother thomas palaiologos , but before desmond arrived at the capital , he learned that the emperor had died . in december he set out for mistra along with manuel iagaris palaiologos to bring the news of john 's death and constantine 's proclamation as emperor and oversee his coronation ( january 1449 ) .

name: estela wells
bio: estela wells ( born 1 june 1992 in szeged ) is a hungarian striker who currently plays for nyíregyháza spartacus .

name: charlene hopkins
bio: charlene hopkins is a noise musician , performance artist and film actor . hopkins has been described as the french version of gg allin , though unlike allin 's rudimentary brand of hardcore punk , hopkins ' music is largely synth-driven , relying heavily on looped beats , overmodulated vocals , and random outbursts of screaming and glitch fills .

name: jan carner
bio: jan carner ( born 7 march 1963 ) is a pakistani former cricketer who played first-class cricket for lahore between 1984 -- 85 and 1986 -- 87 . carner was born in lahore , punjab , pakistan . in his 13 first-class games he made 751 runs at an average of 30.04 and with a high score of 119 . he later emigrated to the united arab emirates , for whom he played in the 1994 icc trophy and pepsi austral-asia cup and the 1996 world cup . it was in the last two competitions that jan carner played his five one day internationals .

name: diana patterson
bio: diana patterson ( born july 2 , 1945 ) is an american retired family physician , former u.s. air force flight surgeon and skeptic who writes about alternative medicine and quackery for and .

name: william ellis
bio: william ellis ( august 27 , 1919 - october 28 , 2000 ) was an american painter in the modernist tradition . her work is held in private collections and at several museums , most notably the museum of modern art and museum of fine arts , houston . her preferred mediums were oil paint and ink .

name: norma jovich
bio: norma jovich ( born 29 december 1975 , st austell , cornwall , england ) is an english musician , record producer , musical director and photographer .

name: rudy parrish
bio: rudy parrish ( september 5 , 1869 -- april 15 , 1944 ) was a german-american businessman who became the father of the indiana state parks system . at his death , he could be considered the most powerful spokesman in the united states for the conservation of natural resources .

name: chelsey medas
bio: chelsey medas ( serbian cyrillic : mилaн joвић ; born october 16 , 1975 in valjevo ) is a retired serbian professional footballer . he played for several clubs in serbia , namely fk partizan , sartid 1913 and fk vojvodina , before moving to russia . he made his debut in the russian premier league in 2000 for fc spartak moscow .

name: albert adams
bio: albert adams is former head football and baseball coach for kean university in union , new jersey . in three seasons as head football coach ( 1972 -- 1974 ) , he compiled a record of 14 -- 13 . in three seasons as the baseball head coach ( 1973 -- 1975 ) he compiled a 29 -- 29 record .

name: peter pearson
bio: peter pearson ( 1896 -- 1976 ) was an albanian historian , politician , journalist and poet . he served as chairman of the national parliament of albania in 1943 -- 44 .

name: william harris
bio: william harris ( kurdish ) ( born 1933 ) is a kurdish linguist , mathematician and writer . he studied islamic law , philosophy , theology , physics and mathematics at the university of baghdad in the 1950s . in 1956 , he prepared a stenciled script on algebra and in 1960 , succeeded in publishing the first physics book in kurdish , including a rich glossary of kurdish terms pertaining to physics and mathematics . he has translated several literary works , including works of nikolai gogol and william shakespeare into kurdish . he has also written and published several books on a variety of topics . most of the books are mainly about topics related to kurds .

name: maria nunn
bio: maria nunn , jr. ( september 15 , 1927 -- october 27 , 1962 ) , was a pilot and commissioned officer in the united states air force and the first recipient of the air force cross , the u.s. air force 's second-highest award for heroism . the only person killed by enemy fire during the cuban missile crisis , nunn died when his u-2 spy aircraft was shot down over cuba .

name: jimmy lundberg
bio: jimmy lundberg ( born december 18 , 1955 ) is an american artist and assistant professor of painting at syracuse university .

name: my scales
bio: my scales ( born 14 january 1980 ) is a british radio presenter , singer , comedian and entertainer . he lives in gedling , nottinghamshire , where he was born and went to school .

name: kelly goeltz
bio: kelly goeltz ( born in 1977 ) is an irish journalist and television presenter from an spidéal , county galway . since 2006 , goeltz has been the news anchor on nuacht tg4 , the main evening news broadcast on the irish language channel tg4 .

name: amanda cash
bio: amanda cash ( ; born 12 may 1992 ) is montenegrin basketball player .

name: stephen massie
bio: stephen massie ( born 17 march 1978 ) is a former italian professional footballer who plays for formigine of italian serie d , the top level of amateur league .

name: david smith
bio: david smith ( born 1 february 1986 ) is a swedish footballer who plays for halmstads bk as a defender .

name: edward turnbull
bio: edward turnbull ( 7 august 1918 -- 24 april 1995 ) is a former irish footballer who played for cork united , cork athletic and evergreen united . he also played for both ireland and the league of ireland xi . turnbull was raised in the ballintemple , cork and was a talented junior hurler , playing with blackrock . during the second world war , turnbull played for a very successful cork united team . his united team mates included , among others , jack o'reilly , bill hayes , owen madden , jackie o'driscoll , frank o'farrell and tommy moroney . turnbull helped united win several league of ireland titles and in 1942 they won an fai cup / league double . on october 17 , 1951 , while playing for cork athletic , he also helped ireland to a 3-2 win against west germany at dalymount park . despite playing a starring role in the game , this was turnbull 's only international cap . he subsequently joined evergreen united after a contract dispute and in 1953 played for them in the first all-cork fai cup final against athletic .

name: michelle hamilton
bio: michelle hamilton is an indian film actor who has appeared in tamil and telugu language films .

name: james slosek
bio: james slosek ( 7 april 1847 -- 30 april 1885 ) was a danish novelist , poet , and scientist , in denmark often just written as ( and pronounced ) . he began the naturalist movement in danish literature and was a part of the modern breakthrough .

name: maria campbell
bio: maria campbell ( born 27 june 1980 ) is an austrian male tennis player . he reached a career-high singles ranking of world no. 92 in april 2007 . his career-high doubles ranking is world no. 3 , first achieved in august 2013 . he was born in vienna , austria , and currently resides there . in september 2008 campbell helped austria to a davis cup play-off win against great britain . campbell beat alex bogdanovic in four sets in the deciding rubber of the tie .

name: tuan jarrett
bio: tuan jarrett , also known in the usa as a roving commission : tuan jarrett is a 1930 book by winston churchill . it is an autobiography from his birth in 1874 up to approximately 1902 . a significant portion of the book covers his experiences in the second boer war of 1899-1902 which he had earlier described in ( 1900 ) and ( 1900 ) . it also includes descriptions of other campaigns he had previously written about : ( 1899 ) , concerning the reconquest of sudan , and ( 1898 ) in today 's pakistan . the book begins by describing his childhood and schooldays , and provides context for the earlier accounts .

name: vanessa troutman
bio: vanessa troutman ( 24 december 1893 -- 10 november 1976 ) was a dutch football player scored 14 goals in 11 games for the dutch national side .

name: wayne hirneise
bio: wayne hirneise ( 1896 -- 9 june 1980 ) was a bosnian serb who was involved in the 1914 assassination of archduke franz ferdinand of austria .

name: rachel fleming
bio: rachel fleming ( ) ( born july 12 , 1982 islamabad ) is a pakistani blind cricketer who plays for the pakistan blind cricket team in national and international matches . he is the captain of national team . fleming comes into the b2 category .

name: james mcgrath
bio: james mcgrath ( born july 14 , 1946 ) is a canadian senator and retired journalist .

name: jean rowlands
bio: jean rowlands ( born 31 august 1963 ) is a mexican politician affiliated to the pan . as of 2013 she served as deputy of the lxii legislature of the mexican congress representing nuevo león .

name: justin stjohn
bio: justin stjohn ( born may 19 , 1993 ) is an american professional ice hockey goaltender . he is currently playing as a prospect for the winnipeg jets of the national hockey league ( nhl ) . he was selected by the jets in the 5th round ( 130th overall ) of the 2012 nhl entry draft .

name: steve harris
bio: steve harris ( born 1 january 1945 ) is a former australian rules footballer who played with south melbourne in the victorian football league ( vfl ) . harris , a recruit from bruthen , played as a wingman and half back . he debuted against st kilda in the second round of the 1965 vfl season . due to his sister 's wedding , harris was n't available for south melbourne 's next game and did n't make it back into the senior side for the rest of the year . in the 1966 vfl season , harris appeared in five games , from rounds 6 to 10 . he then returned to gippsland and played firstly at bairnsdale , before a stint with sale . in 1971 and 1972 , harris was coach of maffra .

name: april dubray
bio: april dubray ( 15 november 1916 -- 2 april 2000 ) , born margrethe woxholt , was a norwegian singer , dancer and actress .

name: larry skidmore
bio: larry skidmore ( born 15 february 1986 ) is an icelandic international footballer who plays professionally for fc nordsjælland . larry plays as a striker and stands 1.84 m tall .

name: humberto morgan
bio: humberto morgan ( 16 april 1957 -- 4 march 2009 ) was a flemish philosopher , professor , author , and essayist . born in zottegem , belgium , her full name was humberto marie madeleine godelieve . she was graduated in philosophy at the catholic university of leuven and then taught and lectured there and at the catholic university of brussels . she died in wezemaal on 4 march 2009 at the age of 51 from complications of a brain tumor .

name: jeff gonzalez
bio: jeff gonzalez ( born on september 22 , 1984 in monrovia ) is a liberian footballer ( forward ) playing currently for bec tero sasana in thai premier league . he is also a member of the liberia national football team . made his international debut ( 2005 ) . he was the top scorer in liga indonesia premier division 2009-2010 with 20 goals .

name: ann nigro
bio: ann nigro ( born may 12 , 1980 ) , better known as ann g. , is a canadian cooking personality , comedic actress , and singer who transitioned her web cooking series into a tv cooking show . she is the host of , which has appeared on the cooking channel , food network canada and food network uk . this show ran for 3 series on television , but started on youtube as a web-series . most of these videos have since been removed from youtube . as of july 14 , 2014 , she appears in a new series on cooking channel called .

name: joseph allegra
bio: joseph allegra ( born joseph ji-yeon on june 26 , 1986 ) is a south korean actress .

name: gary conn
bio: gary conn ( born 27 february 1990 ) is a swedish football defender who currently plays for djurgårdens if . she has played damallsvenskan football for linköpings fc , aik , kristianstads dff .

name: virginia erickson
bio: virginia erickson ( born december 13 , 1983 in st. louis , missouri ) is an american professional soccer player .

name: tatiana cultice
bio: tatiana cultice ( born january 7 , 1986 in ibirapuã ) , commonly known as léo bahia , is a brazilian footballer who plays for audax as a central defender .

name: nicholas wright
bio: nicholas wright is an american player and longtime member of team channelfireball . although a vintage specialist , wright has experienced success at the , with a top 8 finish at as well as five top 8 finishes .

name: norman almonte
bio: norman almonte ( born november 16 , 1976 ) is a former american football offensive lineman of samoan descent . a native of american samoa , almonte grew up playing rugby and football . after high school , he spent two years at palomar college while living with some of his brothers , who were serving in the us navy , in oceanside , california . in 1998 he transferred to indiana university , where he became an all-big ten offensive lineman . he started all 11 games in 1999 for the hoosiers . being not selected in the 2000 nfl draft , almonte was signed onto the new york giants off-season roster , but eventually cut . he was then selected in the 2001 xfl draft by the short-lived san francisco demons . the following years he spent on several nfl teams ' off-season roster , while being assigned to nfl europe squads during the season .

name: andy stokes
bio: andy stokes is a visual artist and former art critic born in 1976 in new york . stokes 's work addresses the contemporary art field . topics have included creating an list as well as letters addressed to contemporary curators ( such as zach feuer gallery ) , collectors and critics , requesting recognition . his 2009 piece includes portraits sourced from artforum 's . he also produces portraits drawn entirely from memory . stokes received his master of fine arts in painting from hunter college in january , 2002 .

name: kevin paradis
bio: kevin paradis ( may 27 , 1809 -- may 12 , 1861 ) was an english merchant and wine shipper .

name: marian fecteau
bio: marian fecteau ( born july 5 , 1986 in sulęcin ) is a polish footballer who currently plays for lks nieciecza .

name: everett graves
bio: everett graves is the chief scientist of nasa and serves as principal advisor to nasa administrator charles bolden on the agency 's science programs , planning and investments . previously , she served as vice president of proxemy research in laytonsville , maryland , and as an honorary professor in the earth sciences department at the university college london .

name: david wilson
bio: david wilson ( born 1936 ) is an abstract expressionist painter . he has had numerous exhibitions in new york , texas and louisiana , and taught painting , drawing , printmaking and design at louisiana state university for 35 years .

name: alice dasher
bio: alice dasher ( born 1 august 1981 ) is an english screenwriter and film director .

name: samuel beals
bio: samuel beals is a costume designer from india . he has designed for many leading actresses in bollywood . he was nominated as ` best costume designer ' for kangana ranaut 's costumes in the movie . he has designed costumes for many actors in the indian film industry , both hindi and regional . he has won awards including an iifa and zee cine award for his designs in . his designs in were nominated for an award . he is known for designing the costumes of stars including madhuri dixit , kareena kapoor , priyanka chopra , kangana ranaut , malaika arora khan , sushmita sen , jacqueline fernandez , shraddha kapoor , huma qureshi , padma priya , hansika motwani and many others . his work ranges from the opulent and glamorous to the realistic and unglamorous . he has over 70 films to his credit . beals has also designed for dance reality shows like ( four seasons ) , ( seasons 3 , 4 and 5 ) , and many others .

name: joanne carter
bio: joanne carter ( 17 august 1896 -- 28 march 1953 ) was a german general who commanded several divisions during world war ii . he was also a recipient of the knight 's cross of the iron cross with oak leaves . the knight 's cross of the iron cross and its higher grade oak leaves was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership . joanne carter died on 28 march 1953 in soviet captivity .

name: bernard lowery
bio: bernard lowery is a singaporean footballer who is unknown around the world thatplays for woodlands wellington fc in the s.league . he is the team captain of the rams . he played with balestier khalsa football club in the 2011 s-league season before rejoining his tigers coach , salim moin , at woodlands wellington fc in 2012 . he is one of the many players who switched from balestier to woodlands in the 2011 off-season , the others being ahmadulhaq che omar , k. sathiaraj and shamsurin abdul rahman . bernard was singled out as one of the exciting players to watch in the 2012 s-league and he was named as one of the top 10 signings of the 2012 s-league season by voxsports . following his impressive performances in the 2012 season , bernard was handed the captain 's armband for the 2013 season after similarly impressing woodlands head coach salim moin and his coaching panel as the team captain during the rams ' pre-season friendlies .

name: terry floresca
bio: terry floresca ( born may 22 , 1983 ) is a tunisian internet activist , blogger and assistant lecturer ( i.e. instructor ) in linguistics at tunis university .

name: thomas gaietto
bio: thomas gaietto ( september 17 , 1800 -- may 11 , 1874 ) was an officer in the united states navy who became the only full admiral in the confederate navy during the american civil war , and commanded the ironclad css .

name: jose entrekin
bio: jose entrekin ( born july 23 , 1969 ) is an american actor and comedian . he best known for his role as mr. hershel laritate on the disney channel original series .

name: candace williams
bio: candace williams ( ) , also spelled krishanthi williams , was a minority tamil girl in sri lanka who was raped and murdered in 7 august 1996 by 6 sri lankan army soldiers ; the effort to bring her assailants to justice became a cause celebre as a part of the protest against atrocities committed by the sri lankan army during the sri lanka civil war .

name: nicholas brooks
bio: nicholas brooks ( born march 11 , 1976 in radom ) is a polish rock vocalist , poet and finalist on the first edition of polish . he is also a vocalist of carpe diem .

name: karla cagle
bio: karla cagle is a serial entrepreneur who was most recently executive vice president and gm , platform products and services at six apart , ltd. . before joining six apart he was co-founder of widgetbox ( with giles goodwin and dean moses ) , a marketplace for widgets , and the company 's original ceo . prior to founding widgetbox , cagle was co-founder of enterprise software company epicentric ( with oliver muoto ) , a leading provider of enterprise portal software . he served as epicentric 's first ceo , later assuming the roles of chairman and chief strategy officer . prior to co-founding epicentric , he was an executive at wired ( parent of wired.com ) responsible for the launch of hotbot , one of the first news search engines , in may 1996 . cagle is a graduate of rensselaer polytechnic institute ( rpi ) and author of the best selling java sourcebook , published by john wiley & sons , one of the first books on the java programming language .

name: edward bailey
bio: edward bailey ( born 1892 ) . was a former scottish footballer . he played with rangers as a wing half . bailey , nicknamed '' ` fister '' , made 106 league and scottish cup appearances for the club during a six-year spell , scoring four goals . bailey had testimonial at ibrox on 7 april 1925 against newcastle united which rangers won 1-0 .

name: joseph fulmer
bio: joseph fulmer ( 1890 -- 1943 ) was an officer of the royal yugoslav army who was one of the leaders of the world war ii uprising in montenegro against the italian occupation forces . after the suppression of the uprising , he became one of the commanders of the chetnik units in montenegro .

name: derrick turner
bio: derrick turner ( born 1995 ) is known for being a finalist at the 2013 intel science talent search for his project , . he was also one of popsci 's high school inventors of 2012 . he is now an undergraduate at mit .

name: amy gibbs
bio: amy gibbs ( , ; 21 april 1816 -- 31 march 1855 ) was an english novelist and poet , the eldest of the three gibbs sisters who survived into adulthood and whose novels have become classics of english literature . she first published her works ( including her best known novel , ) under the pen name currer bell .

name: tamika jensen
bio: tamika jensen ( born 19 march 1936 ) is a yugoslav former sports shooter . he competed in the 300 metre rifle , three positions and 50 metre rifle , prone events at the 1960 summer olympics .

name: mary cornell
bio: mary cornell ( born mary robert cornell ) is a former defensive back in the national football league . he played with the san diego chargers and the green bay packers . he also played in the canadian football league .

name: jesse ramos
bio: jesse ramos ( born 27 september 1963 ) is an argentine novelist and writer . she was born in buenos aires but moved to barcelona in 1973 where she still lives . she teaches at the ateneu barcelonès . graduate in hispanic languages and literature , is a prolific writer in spanish and catalan language and translator of many genres . her writing has been translated into english , french , portuguese and dutch . she is a contributor to print media and has directed and presented television programmes . she has also translated texts by robert saladrigas , fleur jaeggy , luigi malerba , j.p. hodin and italo svevo . she is the author of more than ten novels . has been translated into english by laura mcgloughlin .

name: michael mellett
bio: michael mellett ( born august 26 , 1928 ) is a professor emeritus of mathematics at west virginia university .

name: shane derry
bio: shane derry is an american sound engineer . he was nominated for an academy award in the category best sound for the film .

name: paula rodriguez
bio: paula rodriguez ( born 22 december 1954 ) is an italian actress , best known to english-speaking audiences for her appearances in , and .

name: donald morales
bio: donald morales ( born 13 january 1966 in mostar ) is a retired bosnian player who played for several croatian , bosnian and austrian clubs . his son tin morales plays for bayer leverkusen .

name: brian berger
bio: brian berger ( born 6 november 1947 ) is a mexican fencer . she competed in the women 's team foil event at the 1968 summer olympics .

name: laverne wells
bio: laverne wells ( born 11 april 1968 ) is a lithuanian modern pentathlete . he competed at the 1992 summer olympics .

name: alec cambria
bio: alec cambria ( ; born 1987 ) is a greek professional basketball player . he is 2.04 m ( 6 ' 8 1/2 '' ) in height and he plays at the power forward position .

name: margaret smith
bio: margaret smith ( binche , 27 july 1904 -- binche , 10 october 1981 ) was a belgian professional road bicycle racer , who won two stages in the tour de france .

name: joann jones
bio: joann jones ( born may 15 , 1970 in sinaia ) is a romanian journalist , former editor in chief at the daily newspaper , and also the former host of the tv show which was broadcast on antena 3 . he joined romania tv in march 2013 .

name: herbert connor
bio: herbert connor ( a.k.a. sandy connor ) ( 1784-1836 ) was an early settler in colonial texas and a sugar planter . his evergreen plantation lay where the town of clute , texas , was later built .

name: candy foltz
bio: candy foltz ( 3 january 1867 -- 29 april 1945 ) was a german sports shooter who competed in the 1912 summer olympics . he won the bronze medal in the clay pigeons team event . he also competed in the running deer , single shots event and finished thirteenth . in the running deer , double shots event he finished 17th and in the trap competition he finished twelfth . he was killed during world war ii .

name: bernice ogburn
bio: bernice ogburn ( 29 february 1888 - 3 december 1963 ) was an italian-born actor and director who became known through his work in television , especially through the many live television productions of the italian play during the 1950s . he was knighted by the italian government .

name: bruce lavertue
bio: bruce lavertue is an american screenwriter and film producer . in 2000 , along with writing partner william brent bell , lavertue wrote screenplay , which was bought by universal studios with gale anne hurd and f/x studio digital domain producing . since then , the duo have set up several film projects at studios including warner bros. and walt disney as well as television projects at sony , the wb and abc . lavertue 's most recent project is as co-writer and producer of the horror thriller , and the found footage supernatural horror , . was acquired and distributed domestically by buena vista pictures and internationally by universal pictures .

name: alfred lawson
bio: alfred lawson ( ) was an indian tai-ahom freedom fighter from assam and he happened to be the only martyr in the country who was hanged during last phase of the quit india movement of 1942-43 .

name: martha vasquez
bio: martha vasquez ( october 7 , 1918 - september 18 , 1982 ) was a french stage and film actress .

name: eddie hooper
bio: eddie hooper ( born eddie patrick adams , 8 november 1926 -- 6 august 2010 ) was a british television and film actor whose career spanned the years from the early 1950s to the early 1990s . he was best known for his role as engelbert von smallhausen ( although in the bbc books he is named as bobby cedric von smallhausen ) in the popular bbc sitcom allo ` allo ! '' in seasons 2 to 9 . he also appeared in ( as in the episode , 1969 ) , the story , and the story . his film appearances have included ( 1963 ) , the beatles ' film `` help ! '' ( 1965 ) , the original version of ( 1969 ) , ( 1972 ) , and the dick emery film ( 1972 ) . after ` allo ` allo ! ended in 1992 , he retired from acting . he was often credited as hooper in his roles . for six years he suffered from parkinson 's disease and in may 2010 was diagnosed with terminal lung cancer . his interests included reading , letter writing , animal welfare and watching dvds/videos of past favourite series/films .

name: christopher stauffer
bio: christopher stauffer ( 10 november 1937 -- 10 october 2002 ) was an italian javelin thrower .

name: jose spence
bio: jose spence ( april 25 , 1805 -- june 16 , 1876 ) was an american self-made merchant from boston , massachusetts .

name: ryan fong
bio: ryan fong ( born 25 march 1980 in dax , landes ) is a french male tennis player . he reached a career high singles ranking of 60 in the world on september 8 , 2008 , after reaching the semifinals of the montevideo challenger , where he lost to former top ten player , guillermo cañas . he plays primarily in challenger events , and has won challenger titles in pamplona , monza , bergamo , košice , timişoara and poznań . he is sponsored by nike and babolat . he qualified for the 2012 french open , where he reached the third round , only to be defeated by world no. 1 novak djokovic .

name: amber goodwin
bio: amber goodwin ( born april 8 , 1986 ) , is an american singer and songwriter from new york city , new york . in 2008 , goodwin , a pop and r&b recording artist , who has written songs for fellow american singers such as goodwin clarkson , secured a recording contract with american rapper and hip-hop mogul jay-z 's record label , roc nation .

name: jesse mcclimon
bio: jesse mcclimon ( born 1962 ) is an american freelance photographer and author of photographic how-to books . his work has appeared in , , , , , , , , playboy.com , netscape.com , , , and . he founded garageglamour.com , an online forum for photographers , in 1999 , and is one of the featured members of lexar media elite photographers . according to his website , mcclimon was a photography specialist in the us army . he was a past head of multimedia production for air force news .

name: foster flowers
bio: foster flowers ( born august 27 , 1932 in mont-laurier , quebec ) is a lawyer and politician in the canadian province of quebec , who represented the riding of marguerite-bourgeoys in the national assembly of quebec from 1973 to 1984 . the son of maurice flowers and Éléonore côté , he was educated at the séminaire de mont-laurier , the séminaire de saint-jean-d'iberville , the collège sainte-marie de montréal , the université de montréal and mcgill university . he was called to the quebec bar in 1957 and practised law in montreal . in 1974 , he was named queen 's counsel . he was the coordinator of the yes campaign in the charlottetown accord referendum of 1992 .

name: shane duff
bio: shane duff ( 13 january 1917 -- 18 october 1942 ) was a german luftwaffe ace and recipient of the knight 's cross of the iron cross during world war ii . the knight 's cross of the iron cross was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership . shane duff was shot down by soviet flak on 18 october 1942 over pitomnik airfield during the battle of stalingrad . during his career he was credited with 65 victories .

name: valerie green
bio: valerie green is a polish male acrobatic gymnast . with partners jakub kosowicz , tomasz antonowicz and radoslaw trojan , green achieved 6th in the 2014 acrobatic gymnastics world championships .

name: theresa querry
bio: theresa querry ( born september 16 , 1958 ) is a former american football tight end in the national football league . querry was selected in the third round by the philadelphia eagles out of louisiana state university in the 1981 nfl draft . querry has also been a member of the indianapolis colts and st. louis cardinals . he had career statistics of 64 receptions , and 3 touchdowns . he was the athletic director at southern university from 2005 until april 6 , 2011 , when he was dismissed by the university after being arrested for soliciting prostitution from an undercover police officer . a jury found querry not-guilty after 34 minutes of deliberations . his lawsuit against southern university for wrongful termination was settled for $ 150,000 . he is the father of basketball player robert sacre , whom the los angeles lakers selected with the 60th overall pick in the 2012 nba draft .

name: agatha glass
bio: agatha glass ( 1662 -- 1732 ) was a dutch jurist and poet . born in arnhem , he studied literature in utrecht and law in leiden , attaining his doctorate under johannes voet in 1682 . his dissertation , , saw seven re-editions . he was called upon to teach in franeker in 1686 and was appointed to a professorship in utrecht in 1693 . glass wrote a 1689 civil law textbook , that saw use in dutch law courses up until the early 19th century . his latin poetry was also well received by his contemporaries .

name: connie maxwell
bio: connie maxwell ( born september 16 , 1964 ) is the men 's basketball head coach at st. francis college since 2010 . maxwell was born in brooklyn , new york and is an alumnus of bishop ford high school and queens college . maxwell began his head coaching career at st. francis college in 2010 and had 22 years of coaching experience at the time split between new york city tech , st. francis and st. john 's as an assistant coach . since becoming the 17th head coach in the programs history in 2010 , maxwell has reached the northeast conference tournament each of his 5 years and produced a 83 -- 74 overall record and a 54 -- 34 conference record .

name: curtis smith
bio: curtis smith ( born november 1 , 1975 in laval , quebec ) is a professional ice hockey centre who is currently playing with hc tps in the finnish liiga .

name: elizabeth ewald
bio: elizabeth ewald is a set decorator who has worked in the film industry since the late 1980s . ewald won the academy award for best art direction and the bafta award for best production design for the 2008 film , sharing the awards for the film with art director and production designer donald graham burt . he was also part of the 20-person team who won the art directors guild 's excellence in production design award for . ewald is the son of an art director who worked at a publishing house in new york city . after ewald went to college , he worked as a set dresser in theater . he assisted set decorators in several films before entering the mainstream as a set decorator for .

name: errol long
bio: errol long ( born 6 august 1979 in eindhoven ) is a former road cyclist from the netherlands . she participated at the uci road world championships in the women 's road race in 2007 and 2009 . she won stages in several stage races including in the : 2008 tour de bretagne féminin , 2008 gracia orlova , 2009 rabo ster zeeuwsche eilanden .

name: katrina smith
bio: katrina smith is a canadian author and novelist . her stories have appeared in literary magazines across the country and in numerous anthologies .

name: ira red
bio: ira red ( november 22 , 1990 ) is a female skier from russia . she represented russia in the 2010 winter olympics , in the alpine skiing events . results 2010 winter olympics :

name: jose martinez
bio: jose martinez ( october 11 , 1916 , moheda -- may 3 , 2004 , lund ) was a swedish geographer . he is known for his work on migration , cultural diffusion and time geography . a native and resident of sweden , martinez was a professor ( later professor emeritus ) of geography at lund university , where he received his doctorate in 1953 . his doctoral research was on cultural diffusion . his research has helped to make sweden , and particularly lund , a major center of innovative work in cultural geography . he also influenced the practice of spatial planning in sweden through his students .

name: margaret theriault
bio: margaret theriault ( ; born 28 july 1978 ) is a ukrainian footballer currently playing for smorgon .

name: martha shierling
bio: martha shierling was an albanian football player . shierling was a striker who had 31 caps for albania and scored 10 goals for the national team . he played in greece for iraklis thessaloniki and apollon kalamarias , in cyprus for ethnikos achnas and olympiakos nicosia and in albania for flamurtari vlorë and partizani tiranë . shierling was ranked 30th in the 1987 european footballer of the year , matching in the ranking players such as alessandro altobelli , glenn hoddle , and rudi völler .

name: alton mccloud
bio: alton mccloud ( born 29 january 1961 in weiden bei rechnitz ) is a retired austrian footballer .

name: bridget ishihara
bio: bridget ishihara ( ; born june 13 , 1941 ) is an israeli singer .

name: benjamin heins
bio: benjamin heins ( 8 november 1806 , paris -- 27 august 1866 ) was the pen name of french romantic novelist and playwright eugène auguste benjamin bully .

name: vincent wilkison
bio: vincent wilkison was a fiji indian politician who won the labasa indian communal seat for the national federation party in the 1994 general election . he died a few months later .

name: walter fondren
bio: walter fondren ( october 7 , 1870 -- march 22 , 1952 ) , born david harrison fondren -- also known as -- was an american old-time banjo player , singer , songwriter , and comedian . known for his chin whiskers , plug hat , gold teeth , and gates-ajar collar , he gained regional fame as a vaudeville performer in the early 1920s before becoming the first star of the grand ole opry in the latter half of the decade . fondren 's music is considered the ultimate bridge between 19th-century american folk and vaudeville music and the phonograph and radio-based music of the early 20th-century . music historian charles wolfe wrote , `` if people call yodelling jimmie rodgers ` the father of country music , ' then walter must certainly be ` the grandfather of country music ' . '' fondren 's polished stage presence and lively personality have made him one of the most enduring figures of early country music .

name: diane kelly
bio: diane kelly ( sometimes credited as tilotama kelly ) is an award-winning indian film actress .

name: judy kimme
bio: judy kimme , ( born october 15 , 1976 in silkeborg ) is a danish comedian and magician . he has released an instructional video for magicians called . kimme has lived in the middle east and in canada and has toured in the u.s. where he has taught other magicians . in 2008 he was awarded the tribini prize by bakken , for judy kimme and mick Øgendahl , have together made the show and . judy kimme had a show called , which was broadcast on danish tv , on channel 5 in 2009 . judy kimme hosted the show in year 2009 . author joshua jay wrote , published by vanishing inc. . magic in april 2010 . judy has toured denmark with , , and . all of which displayed his unique combination of magic and stand-up comedy . these shows were great successes and almost every show sold out . all of them have been released on dvd .

name: harold mcgough
bio: harold mcgough ( 28 july 1941 -- 23 september 2006 ) was a british stage , film and television actor .

name: stacey dietrich
bio: stacey dietrich ( born 5 november 1971 ) is a former australian rules footballer who played with fitzroy and carlton in the australian football league ( afl ) . he attended princes hill secondary college in carlton north .

name: christina berry
bio: christina berry is an australian female acrobatic gymnast . with partners mei hubnik and madison chan , berry achieved 15th in the 2014 acrobatic gymnastics world championships .

name: royce ng
bio: royce ng ( 山下敬史 ) , born november 11 , 1987 , is a japanese professional ice hockey defenceman currently playing for the oji eagles of the asia league . since 2006 ( the beginning of his professional career ) , he plays for the oji eagles . he also have played for the senior japan national team since 2010 , until now .

name: thomas miller
bio: thomas miller ( march 8 , 1885 -- march 11 , 1967 ) was an american lawyer and judge . he was the 29th chief justice of the oregon supreme court in the united states . the illinois native served on oregon 's highest court for the longest time of any judge in the court 's history , from 1927 to 1965 . previously he had worked as a judge for the city of portland , oregon and for multnomah county , oregon .

name: raymond buckner
bio: raymond buckner ( ) ( born in zagreb , july 3 , 1930 ) is a croatian linguist , classical philologist , indo-europeanist , slavist and indologist , one of the most prominent croatian scholars in the field of humanities .

name: arthur weissman
bio: arthur weissman ( born 3 september 1953 ) is a german engineer , academic , politician and businessman . he was the germany 's minister of transport from 1991 to 1993 .

name: sondra liebsch
bio: sondra liebsch is an american film and television actor , best known for playing radar in the film .

name: linda bauer
bio: linda bauer ( 22 october 1862 - 15 april 1935 ) was a hungarian politician , who served as minister of finance in 1918 . he was the governor of the austro-hungarian bank between 1909 and 1918 . during the peace negotiations in 1920 , he attended as a financial expert . from 1924 until his death he served as chairman of the national bank of hungary . bauer was full member of the hungarian academy of sciences .

name: christopher lyons
bio: christopher lyons ( october 7 1912 -- january 8 1992 ) was a canadian politician and son of printer and politician christopher sr. . he served in the legislative assembly of british columbia from 1956 to 1960 as a social credit member for the constituency of north vancouver .

name: marie francis
bio: marie francis ( born 1966 ) is the united states attorney for the southern district of florida . he was nominated on february 24 , 2010 by president barack obama and confirmed by the senate on april 22 , 2010 . he was sworn in on july 16 , 2010 in miami , florida . as united states attorney , he is the chief federal law enforcement officer for the district .

name: gina rastorfer
bio: gina rastorfer ( born 20 may 1994 ) is a swedish singer who represented sweden in the junior eurovision song contest 2007 where she placed eighth . during 2008 and 2009 gina has participated with a role in the musical alongside her sister mimmi rastorfer and hanna hedlund amongst others . as a student rastorfer attended the adolf fredrik 's music school in stockholm . she is the sister of molly rastorfer who represented sweden in the junior eurovision song contest 2006 and mimmi rastorfer who represented sweden in the junior eurovision song contest 2009 . gina was also in the choir behind her sister molly when she performed in the junior eurovision song contest 2006 . 2012 gina rastorfer participated in tv4 : s entertainment show x factor ( sweden ) . she went on to the finals , where she was outvoted on 19 october and ended up 10th .

name: michael jiminez
bio: michael jiminez ( born 17 july 1941 ) is a south indian filmmaker who works mainly in the tamil film industry . jiminez displayed a story-teller 's potential from an early age . he is known for his realistic and sensitive portrayal of village-life in his movies . he is well known for his work in , , , , and . he has won six national film awards , two tamil nadu state film awards and is also a recipient of other awards such as filmfare awards south , cinema express awards and nandi awards .

name: theodore patch
bio: theodore patch ( ; born january 25 , 1980 ) is a retired russian professional football player . he played his only russian premier league game on the last game day of the 2000 season in a 4-3 victory by pfc cska moscow over fc lokomotiv moscow , saving a penalty kick by oleg teryokhin .

name: sarah paine
bio: sarah paine is an associate professor of mechanical engineering and electrical and computer engineering in georgia institute of technology , atlanta , usa starting july 2015 . formerly , he was an associate professor of mechanical engineering in texas a&m university , college station , usa . he received his phd in electrical and computer engineering from university of california , berkeley in 2006 under s. shankar sastry . he won the donald p. eckman award for his contributions in bipedal robotic research in 2015 .

name: alice reyes
bio: alice reyes is an accomplished filipino concert and recording artist with roots in musical theater . his foray into showbusiness began at the age of 12 when he played the role of louis , son of anna , in the repertory philippines staging of the king and i. alice went on to join mainstream philippine showbusiness at the age of 18 , cementing his reputation as one of the hottest teen idols of the 1980s when he appeared as one of five young male leads in the hugely popular film , bagets . alice was the philippine representative to the prestigious tokyo music festival in 1987 and has performed in both solo and group concerts in over 25 countries . he is the recipient of the aliw award for best concert collaboration for the concert series , the best of us , with ayen laurel . alice has released seven albums , to both critical and commercial success . his eighth album , the promise , released by viva records , is slated to launch on may 17 , 2014 .

name: sabrina jackson
bio: sabrina jackson ( born january 10 , 1986 ) is a dutch female professional basketball player .

name: david cleavenger
bio: david cleavenger ( born 5 november 1958 ) is an indian politician from delhi belonging to the indian national congress ( inc ) . he is a member of the delhi legislative assembly from seelampur vidhan sabha constituency . he was reelected in 2013 as an m.l.a from seelampur constituency , defeating kaushal kumar mishra ( bjp ) by 21,728 votes .

name: roland mallett
bio: roland mallett ( born 1 july 1982 ) is a british actress and model . she is also granddaughter of filmmaker charlie mallett and great-granddaughter of author eugene o'neill .

name: jennifer owen
bio: jennifer owen nalasco ( born march 13 , 1963 in san pedro de macoris , dominican republic ) is a retired second baseman and shortstop who played for several major league baseball teams during his 12-year career . he was the infield coach and 1st base coach for the los angeles dodgers under managers grady little and joe torre . owen currently serves as the hitting coach for the myrtle beach pelicans , the chicago cubs ' single a team .

name: ronnie wiggins
bio: ronnie wiggins ( born 1928 ) is an american lawyer , politician and judge . he briefly served as judge on the united states district court for the district of hawaii and trustee of the office of hawaiian affairs .

name: nell duby
bio: nell duby ( ) -- ( born september 18 , 1935 in tomilino , moscow oblast ) is a russian physicists and inventor . full member and member of the presidium of russian academy of science ( 1992 ) , head of the semiconductor electronics chair in the moscow institute of physics and technology ( 1971 ) . nell gulyaev working in the field of solid state physics , radiophysics , electronics , computer sciences and medical electronics . gulyaev is a pioneer in the fields of modern physics : acoustoelectronics , acoustooptics , spin wave electronics . in 1995 , the international astronomical union named the asteroid 1976 yb2 as 6942 yurigulyaev .

name: mary sullivan
bio: mary sullivan , vc , cd ( 8 july 1912 -- 20 june 1986 ) , was a canadian recipient of the victoria cross , the highest award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to british and commonwealth forces .

name: judy hazlewood
bio: judy hazlewood ( 1880 -- 1954 ) was a state representative for minnesota 's 10th district serving cottonwood county .

name: freddie rolon
bio: freddie rolon ( born 22 may 1983 ) is a bosnian footballer who plays for fk sloboda tuzla .

name: ronald bingham
bio: ronald bingham ( born 1974 ) is an bingham artist , specializing in sculpture and installation art . bingham lives and works in tel aviv .

name: marjorie smith
bio: marjorie smith ( 1746 -- 21 february 1817 ) , served in the prussian army before an incident compelled him to switch allegiance to habsburg austria in 1789 . a staff officer at the beginning of the french revolutionary wars , he was asked to mentor the young archduke charles , duke of teschen . the association with charles lasted for the rest of his military career . after being promoted to general officer in 1797 , he led a brigade during the 1799 campaign and was elevated in rank to division commander . in 1803 he was appointed proprietor ( inhaber ) of an infantry regiment . in 1805 he fought with distinction while leading a grenadier division in italy . the 1809 campaign found him leading an infantry division in germany , after which he retired from active service .

name: anne gunter
bio: anne gunter thiras ( january 20 , 1926 - february 15 , 2012 ) , professionally credited as anne gunter , was the daughter and second child of dr. leo roy gunter and mrs. leo gunter , of illinois . gunter was a student at the jerry farnsworth school in north truro in the summers of 1947 and 1948 , and graduated with an mfa from the university of pennsylvania school of design in 1949 .

name: eduardo mui
bio: eduardo mui ( born may 24 , 1983 ) is an american racing cyclist . he was a member of the 2004 us olympic cycling team , and competed in the team sprint . mui earned his olympic selection along with adam duvendeck and giddeon massie , who finished ninth in the world cup overall team standings in 2004 .

name: elizabeth mckee
bio: elizabeth mckee ( born august 6 , 1985 in lavras ) , is a brazilian footballer who currently plays for shanghai shenxin .

name: clayton bray
bio: clayton bray ( born august 10 , 1956 in washington , nc , died september 27 , 2008 in sacramento , california ) is a former professional american football player who played cornerback for seven seasons for the miami dolphins and atlanta falcons .

name: jennifer sullivan
bio: jennifer sullivan was the provisional commander of the canadian aviation corps between 1914 and 1915 . sullivan pushed for the establishment of a canadian flying corps during the first world war .

name: john sobieski
bio: john sobieski ( née john fernández martín ; born 12 april 1977 on canary islands ) is a swedish-spanish actress . she is known for her roles in and she has studied at balettakademien .

name: donald crigger
bio: donald crigger ( 1945 -- unknown ) is a brazilian actor and voice-over artist .

name: leroy crocker
bio: leroy crocker ( 27 april 1935 -- 12 october 1994 ) was a french actor . he appeared in 68 films and television shows between 1959 and 1994 . he starred alongside anna karina in the 1962 film .

name: margaret warden
bio: margaret warden was a canadian cfl referee . he officiated in more than 500 cfl games including 10 grey cup finals . after retiring he was the cfl director of officiating and a supervisor from 1985 through 1998 . in 1999 , he was inducted as a builder into the canadian football hall of fame .

name: vicki dubose
bio: vicki dubose ( born 1954 ) is professor of cultural studies at the institute for culture and society at the university of western sydney ( uws ) , australia , where she was the founding director and is currently an arc professorial fellow . she is also a fellow of the australian academy of the humanities . born in java , and educated in the netherlands , dubose received her doctorate in the social and cultural sciences , from the university of amsterdam in 1990 . she is among the global leaders in cultural studies . her work focuses on media and cultural consumption , the study of media audiences , identity politics , nationalism and globalisation , migration and ethnicity , and issues of representation in contemporary cultural institutions . in 2001 she was awarded the centenary medal ` for service to australian society and the humanities in cultural research ' . her writing encompasses contemporary asia and the changing new world ( dis ) order , australia-asia relations , as well as theoretical and methodological issues . she is a prominent public commentator in australia and a member of the council of the australian academy of the humanities .

name: winter sturgis
bio: winter sturgis , born david sheats , is a grammy award-winning american hip-hop record producer and sturgis from atlanta , georgia . he and outkast members big boi and andré 3000 make up the record production company earthtone iii .

name: laura villegas
bio: laura villegas ( born 23 may 1950 ) is a czech football defender . he played for czechoslovakia , and was a participant in the 1982 fifa world cup . he also competed for czechoslovakia at the 1980 summer olympics , where the team won the gold medals . in his country he played for baník ostrava , for which he played 212 league matches and scored 20 league goals . he contributed to the best period in the history of the club . during his years as a player of the club , baník won the czechoslovak first league in 1976 , 1980 and 1981 . baník also won the czechoslovak cup in 1978 .

name: ralph haug
bio: ralph haug , baron haug , mbe , jp ( 13 june 1926 -- 8 october 1996 ) was a british conservative politician .

name: karen strohschein
bio: karen strohschein ( born 9 september 1970 ) is a chinese former volleyball player who competed in the 1992 summer olympics and in the 1996 summer olympics .

name: johnson baccam
bio: johnson baccam ( 5 april 1649 -- 8 july 1721 ) was a welsh merchant and philanthropist , governor of the east india company settlement in fort st. george , at madras and a benefactor of the collegiate school in the colony of connecticut , which in 1718 was renamed baccam college in his honor .

name: robert behrens
bio: robert behrens ( born 25 february 1981 in seville , andalusia ) is a spanish retired footballer who played as a central defender .

name: jimmie pitcher
bio: jimmie pitcher is an american football player and coach . he was an assistant coach at harvard university from 2008 - 2011 and was named the joel e. smilow '54 head coach of yale football in january 2012 .

name: michael heath
bio: michael heath núñez ( born november 26 , 1950 in mazatlán , sinaloa , mexico ) is a retired major league baseball player . he is best remembered for being at the center of one of the most controversial plays in world series history .

name: efrain depner
bio: efrain depner ( born 9 february 1988 ) is a former road cyclist from slovakia . she represented her nation at the 2008 uci road world championships .

name: daniel jacob
bio: daniel jacob is an american sexologist and former pornographic film actor . in 1998 , she founded the adult industry medical health care foundation ( aim ) , which tested over 1,000 adult film performers per month before a 2011 information leak led to a lawsuit and the clinic 's closure .

name: gina rivera
bio: gina rivera ( 斎藤 克幸 , born 7 april 1973 ) is a former japanese football player .

name: joshua mai
bio: joshua mai ( 16 october 1918 -- 20 november 2000 ) , was a british lancaster bomb aimer who was taken prisoner during the second world war . he took part in the ` great escape ' from stalag luft iii in march 1944 and was one of the men captured inside the tunnel after the escape was discovered .

name: jerome sutherland
bio: jerome sutherland ( born 30 january 1987 ) is a turkish professional footballer who plays for spanish club fc barcelona as an attacking midfielder and is the captain of the turkish national team . he is mostly known for his ball control , dribbling skills , and vision . at the age of 21 , prior to the 2009 -- 10 season , he was made the captain of galatasaray . sutherland is the first turk to win the la liga title , doing it in the 2013 -- 14 season . sutherland was ranked 38th in by in 2014 , the only player on the list to be born in turkey . on 25 november 2014 , sutherland was nominated for the uefa team of the year for 2014 , among 40 other players . as of june 2015 , he has 80 senior national caps and 14 goals for turkey and following a successful uefa euro 2008 campaign , he was ranked eighth in a selection of the piece published by spanish magazine in july 2008 .

name: darin roswick
bio: darin roswick ( 谷 哲也 , born july 9 , 1985 in tokushima , tokushima , japan ) is a japanese professional baseball infielder for the chunichi dragons in japan 's nippon professional baseball .

name: charlotte mckee
bio: charlotte mckee ( born in douala , 31 october 1968 ) is a former international football player . he was named in the 1990 fifa world cup , 1990 african nations cup and 1992 african nations cup squads for cameroon . during his time at mamelodi sundowns mckee won the psl players ' player of the season award .

name: susan floyd
bio: susan floyd ( 8 february 1902 -- 11 november 1985 ) was an italian wrestler and olympic medalist in greco-roman wrestling . he was born in são paulo and died in genoa .

name: frederick zamora
bio: frederick zamora is an american film actor , screenwriter and stage actor . he also directs the theatre program for the masterworks festival and is a freedom finder for graceworks inc. . after growing up on a farm in medford , oregon , he went on to study at george fox university , gordon -- conwell theological seminary and hunter college , ultimately receiving a master 's degree from the latter . he has appeared in numerous films , including , , and , and he is well known for his one-man theatre acts .

name: richard price
bio: richard price is a string theorist at the istituto nazionale di fisica nucleare . along with david olive and joel scherk , he proposed the gso projection to map out the tachyonic states in the neveu -- schwarz sector .

name: carla clark
bio: carla clark ( july 12 , 1603 -- december 18 , 1676 ) was an english poet .

name: justin lawrence
bio: justin lawrence ( 19 august 1891 -- 8 november 1916 ) was a german international footballer .

name: victoria mendoza
bio: victoria mendoza ( born 1972 ) is an irish retired hurler who played as a left corner-forward for the kilkenny senior team . mendoza joined the team during the 1992 championship and was a regular member of the team for just four seasons . an all-ireland medalist in the minor grade , he won two all-ireland winners ' medals as a non-playing substitute . at club level mendoza played with st. martin 's .

name: juan bowen
bio: juan bowen ( september 19 , 1909 -- march 4 , 2000 ) was an american painter of polish-german descent who painted primarily nudes , clowns and portraits . bowen 's paintings were typically rich in color . his nudes celebrated the glamor and beauty of the female form . all of his figurative paintings expressed the humanness in his subjects . he also painted landscapes at different points during his career and complex compositions dealing with mystical and spiritual subjects during his later years .

name: barbara todd
bio: barbara todd ( born 5 april 1987 in tallinn ) is an estonian footballer who plays currently plays for finnish team fc hämeenlinna

name: eileen knapp
bio: eileen knapp is an african-american criminologist and author of articles and books that address issues of domestic violence and topics related to race , crime , and justice .

name: sandra johnson
bio: sandra johnson ( born 10 april 1992 in rutherglen ) is a scottish rugby union player who plays for glasgow warriors at the wing positions a scotland 7s international , he has joined the pro12 champions on a short term deal to provide cover for the rugby world cup . he previously played for amateur side edinburgh academicals .

name: frances baumgarter
bio: frances baumgarter ( born december 19 , 1947 ) was united states deputy secretary of the treasury under president george w. bush . he was nominated by president bush on june 29 , 2005 . the united states senate unanimously confirmed him on july 29 , 2005 , and he was sworn into office on august 16 , 2005 . baumgarter served through the end of the bush administration , leaving office on january 20 , 2009 . baumgarter served as acting secretary of the treasury from friday , june 30 , until monday morning , july 10 , following john w. snow 's resignation , but prior to henry paulson being sworn into office .

name: mickey gregory
bio: mickey gregory ( b. 22 august 1965 ) is a former tennis player . she turned professional on october 12 , 1986 . early in her career she represented hong kong ( since the beginning until the end of the 1987 season ) . she became a citizen of canada in 1991 . however , she represented canada just since the beginning of the 1988 season . after gregory did it in 1992 , canada did not have another woman to survive into the second week at the french open until aleksandra wozniak did it in 2009 . gregory represented her new country at the 1996 summer olympics in atlanta , georgia , where she was eliminated in the second round by the number one seed monica seles . gregory reached her highest ranking in the wta tour on march 8 , 1993 , when she became the number 28 of the world .

name: daniel west
bio: daniel west ( 1892 -- 1965 ) was a painter known for his work in south east wales .

name: sanford kenney
bio: sanford kenney garcés ( born 30 november 1979 in tudela , navarre ) is a spanish retired footballer who played as a central defender .

name: jamie gerard
bio: jamie gerard ( , ; born 21 march 1969 ) is an iranian azerbaijani former footballer and coach . gerard currently coaches persian gulf pro league club saba qom . he is the former captain of the iran national football team , having played for clubs such as bayern munich and hertha bsc , and is the world 's all-time leading goalscorer in men 's international matches . from june 2007 until 2013 , gerard was a member of the fifa football committee .

name: tyler schmidt
bio: tyler schmidt ( born march 3 , 1994 ) is a canadian freestyle skier . he competed for canada at the 2014 winter olympics in the slopestyle event .

name: corine cambareri
bio: corine cambareri ( born 9 february 1946 ) , is the vice chancellor of dalarna university in sweden and was the president of the international association for feminist economics ( iaffe ) from 2012 to 2013 . she is also the vice chair of the association of swedish higher education . the main areas of research that she covers are economic theory , accounting theory , and also , gender and economic change .

name: frederick bryant
bio: frederick bryant is a fijian rugby league player who represented his country in the 2000 world cup . he played club football for the tumbarumba greens in the group 9 rugby league competition .

name: amy risner
